{"Default Document":"<p class=\"action\">Quiet Hours 3rd Draft</p><p class=\"action\">written by</p><p class=\"action\">Amanda Gikas</p><p class=\"action\">77 Water Oak Way Dallas, Ga 30157</p><p class=\"action\">404-663-4696</p><p class=\"action\">Amandagikas@gmail.com</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 1</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">EXT. CITY ROOFTOP - NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Wind howls around BENJAMIN PRICE (20, tall, heavy-set, curly</p><p class=\"action\">dark hair, piercing blue eyes). He looks wrecked, like he has</p><p class=\"action\">been crying for hours.</p><p class=\"action\">Humidity clings to his skin. Sirens wail faintly below. A</p><p class=\"action\">spotlight from a police cruiser cuts through the dark.</p><p class=\"action\">He stands at the ledge, trembling. Dried tears. Tight chest.</p><p class=\"action\">Voices behind him, urgent but unreal.</p><p class=\"action\">Heat rises off the streets below. The shouting behind him is</p><p class=\"action\">barely there, like it is coming through water.</p><p class=\"character\">POLICE OFFICER (O.S.)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(through megaphone)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We can talk, Benjamin. Just step</p><p class=\"dialogue\">back.</p><p class=\"action\">A hand clamps his arm. He whips around and locks eyes with</p><p class=\"action\">the OFFICER.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let go of me.</p><p class=\"character\">OFFICER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let me help you.</p><p class=\"action\">The officer’s voice stays calm, trained.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You can’t help me. I don’t want</p><p class=\"dialogue\">help. You don’t get to pull me</p><p class=\"dialogue\">back.</p><p class=\"action\">He jerks his arm free.</p><p class=\"action\">The shift in weight is instant. His heel slips.</p><p class=\"action\">The city drops away.</p><p class=\"action\">The officer lunges.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin’s eyes widen. Then blackness swallows him.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HOSPITAL ROOM - UNKNOWN TIME</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin’s eyes snap open. He gasps, chokes, coughs hard.</p><p class=\"action\">Grit and panic claw at his throat.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh. What the fuck?</p><p class=\"action\">White ceiling. Buzzing silence. A sterile, windowless room</p><p class=\"action\">with one wooden bed. Gray clothes folded neatly. No monitors.</p><p class=\"action\">No machines.</p><p class=\"action\">He tries to sit. Winces. Then groans.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Great. I can’t even do that right.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Should’ve picked a higher building.</p><p class=\"action\">He staggers to the door and rattles the knob. Locked.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello.</p><p class=\"action\">Nothing. Movement across the hall. A girl’s wide, blinking <span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">eyes. Then a second figure behind her, smiling like they know </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">him.</span></p><p class=\"action\">A jingle. Keys.</p><p class=\"action\">The door opens. DR. ANNA (30s) enters, luminous and calm,</p><p class=\"action\">unsettlingly still. An ORDERLY looms behind her.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hi, Ben. I’m Anna. I’ve been</p><p class=\"dialogue\">waiting to talk to you.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">My mistake. Do you know where you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">are?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. All I remember is falling, then</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I woke up here.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That must have been terrifying.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ll be back soon.</p><p class=\"action\">She exits. The orderly shuts the door. Click. Then, after a</p><p class=\"action\">beat, it swings open on its own.</p><p class=\"action\">A beat. BENJAMIN steps into the hallway, barefoot.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. WARD HALLWAY - CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Dim green light. Pale floors. Identical rooms, repeating like</p><p class=\"action\">a set.</p><p class=\"action\">He passes a wall of clocks, none ticking. One runs backward.</p><p class=\"action\">He squints — one clock runs backward.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hey, there he is!</p><p class=\"action\">REGAN (20s), curly-haired and bright, skips toward him.</p><p class=\"action\">Mismatched socks. A friendly smile that does not quite reach</p><p class=\"action\">her eyes.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I was wondering when you would wake</p><p class=\"dialogue\">up. I’m Regan.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m Benjamin. Where am I?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They didn’t tell you? Ugh. They</p><p class=\"dialogue\">never do.</p><p class=\"action\">She lowers her voice.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Mental facility. Sort of. Kind of.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s weird here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I'm picking up on that.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(laughs, then softens)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What happened to you?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Life got hard. I wanted out. And</p><p class=\"dialogue\">somebody stopped me.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t say that. Depression lies.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Trust me, I know.</p><p class=\"action\">She gently taps her stomach.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin looks confused.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I just wanted to be thin. Took too</p><p class=\"dialogue\">many pills. Not to die. Just to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">speed things up.</p><p class=\"action\">A beat.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But hey, we’re here. So I guess we</p><p class=\"dialogue\">get another chance?</p><p class=\"action\">She flashes a crooked smile. He almost smiles back, then</p><p class=\"action\">stops himself.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do they let people out of here?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sort of. People disappear. After</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that, nobody can remember their</p><p class=\"dialogue\">names. It’s like they never</p><p class=\"dialogue\">existed.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s not comforting.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Come on. I’ll show you around.</p><p class=\"action\">She reaches for his hand. He hesitates, then takes it. As</p><p class=\"action\">they walk down the hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">A SHADOW passes at the end. Just for a second. Too tall. Too</p><p class=\"action\">slow. Then gone.</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 2</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. CAFETERIA – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">A cold, gray cafeteria. Plastic trays. Flickering fluorescent</p><p class=\"action\">lights.</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN sits alone, toying with a bruised apple.</p><p class=\"action\">A man in a tattered military coat drops onto the bench beside</p><p class=\"action\">him.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re in my spot.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sorry. Didn’t know there were rules</p><p class=\"dialogue\">about seats.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There aren’t. But that one’s mine.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Right. My bad. I’m Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto. Private First Class. Forty-</p><p class=\"dialogue\">second Infantry.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(leans in)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You smell like concrete dust and</p><p class=\"dialogue\">guilt. That’s how you know you're</p><p class=\"dialogue\">fresh.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin gives a faint, uncertain chuckle.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You always talk like that?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Only when I’m awake.</p><p class=\"action\">He scans the walls suspiciously.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t trust the mirrors. They send</p><p class=\"dialogue\">signals. She watches.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She who?</p><p class=\"action\">A voice chimes in from a few seats down.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto, stop scaring the boy. He</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hasn’t even been here 24 hours.</p><p class=\"action\">CARMILLA (60s), regal and out of place in a high-necked</p><p class=\"action\">blouse from another century, sips herbal tea from a chipped</p><p class=\"action\">porcelain cup.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA (TO BENJAMIN) (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If you pray, pray hard. If you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">don’t, now’s a fine time to learn.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Okay. This place just keeps getting</p><p class=\"dialogue\">better.</p><p class=\"action\">From behind them, a sudden BANG! A door slams.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone flinches.</p><p class=\"action\">JACE (30s) stands in the doorway. Hoodie, boots, scars,</p><p class=\"action\">attitude to spare.</p><p class=\"action\">He stares down the room like he owns it. Or wants to burn it</p><p class=\"action\">down.</p><p class=\"action\">He strides past everyone. Tosses a roll onto his tray.</p><p class=\"action\">Doesn’t sit.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s Jace. Don’t bother.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Is he always like that?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Crazy? Dangerous? Probably. Mostly</p><p class=\"dialogue\">just done. Wants out. He’s angry</p><p class=\"dialogue\">all the time. Not even sure what he</p><p class=\"dialogue\">did to get stuck here.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 3</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DOCTOR’S OFFICE – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Dim. Candlelit. Like a séance, not a session.</p><p class=\"action\">DR. ANNA sits cross-legged, hands folded.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello, Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why can’t I call my sister?</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I want to help you. First, what do</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you remember?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I remember the fall. Then here.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s it.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So, you jumped?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Answer my question first. And how</p><p class=\"dialogue\">do you not know that?</p><p class=\"action\">She smiles. Not unkind. Not comforting either.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m so sorry. I have to go. We’ll</p><p class=\"dialogue\">talk again.</p><p class=\"action\">She leaves before he can speak.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 4</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Regan hums, off-key and aimless, outside Benjamin’s room.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What are you doing?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Humming keeps the voices out.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What voices?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The ones in the walls. You’ll hear</p><p class=\"dialogue\">them soon enough.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pauses)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I like your eyes, by the way.</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN looks away nervously.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Thanks. Maybe my one good feature.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t say that. You’ve got more</p><p class=\"dialogue\">going on than you think. Your eyes</p><p class=\"dialogue\">are just loud.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Such a bright soul.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 5</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. GROUP ROOM – NEXT DAY</p><p class=\"action\">A therapy circle: DR. ANNA, BENJAMIN, REGAN, CARMILLA, OTTO,</p><p class=\"action\">AMBER (20s), pale, in fuzzy socks, clutching a stuffed cat.</p><p class=\"character\">DOCTOR</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why are we all here?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">To atone.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">To leave.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">To survive.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">To find my cat. He’s astral</p><p class=\"dialogue\">projecting. I’m following him.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">To talk to my sister. To make</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something right.</p><p class=\"character\">DOCTOR</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Would you take it back? The thing</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that brought you here?</p><p class=\"action\">A moment.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yes. I think I would.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Too late, honey.</p><p class=\"action\">The door creaks open. JACE steps in. Leans against the wall.</p><p class=\"action\">Doesn’t sit.</p><p class=\"character\">DOCTOR</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Jace. Thank you for joining us.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t flatter yourself. I’m just</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here for the drama.</p><p class=\"character\">DOCTOR</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Would you like to speak?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not unless you want to talk about</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the black mold in the East Wing or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the deadbolt someone added to the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">inside of the kitchen freezer.</p><p class=\"action\">Silence.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(softly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He's not wrong.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How long have you been here?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Long enough to know this ain’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">about healing.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(shrugs)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">None of it is. We’re all waiting</p><p class=\"dialogue\">for something. We just don’t know</p><p class=\"dialogue\">what.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe it’s not what. Maybe it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">who.</p><p class=\"action\">A few of them glance at Regan. No one argues.</p><p class=\"action\">A beat.</p><p class=\"action\">Jace meets Benjamin’s eyes.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You're not gonna last here if you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">trust her.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Who? The doctor?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Her. The walls. The mirrors. Any of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it.</p><p class=\"action\">Jace turns and walks out.</p><p class=\"action\">The group begins to disperse.</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN lingers, eyes darting between Regan and the door Jace</p><p class=\"action\">exited through.</p><p class=\"action\">CARMILLA mutters a prayer in Latin.</p><p class=\"action\">OTTO begins pacing in military formation.</p><p class=\"action\">AMBER stays seated. She gently adjusts her plush cat’s ears.</p><p class=\"character\">CONT'D — INT. AMBER’S ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Amber’s room is cluttered, cozy, childlike. Paper stars hang from</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the ceiling. A lava lamp glows. Crayon drawings cover the walls,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">all variations of a cat with glowing eyes.</p><p class=\"action\">She places her stuffed cat on the pillow.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He saw something. He just won’t say.</p><p class=\"action\">She digs through a drawer and pulls out a small metal music box.</p><p class=\"action\">Winds it, but doesn’t open it.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe it’s better if we pretend too.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Just for one more night.</p><p class=\"action\">She climbs into bed. The lights flicker.</p><p class=\"character\">CLICK.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The door she just locked UNLATCHES.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(sits up)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No, thank you. Not tonight.</p><p class=\"action\">Nothing. Silence.</p><p class=\"action\">She reaches for the music box, opens it slowly.</p><p class=\"action\">A tinny, eerie lullaby plays. The notes begin to reverse. Slow.</p><p class=\"action\">Uneven.</p><p class=\"action\">Her walls begin to breathe, subtle at first, like the room itself</p><p class=\"action\">is sighing.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. You’re early.</p><p class=\"action\">She grabs the stuffed cat. Hugs it tight.</p><p class=\"action\">A whisper rides the air, so faint it almost isn’t there.</p><p class=\"character\">WHISPER (V.O.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He opened the wrong door.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber trembles.</p><p class=\"action\">She looks to the window. It’s fogged from the inside. A childlike</p><p class=\"action\">hand print appears on the glass.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (SOFTLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then we have less time than I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">thought.</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 6</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DARK ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin slips through a rusted utility door.</p><p class=\"action\">He’s in a narrow corridor now. Tile gives way to concrete.</p><p class=\"action\">Lights buzz and flicker. A heavy metal door creaks open.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. UNKNOWN ROOM – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">A strange room, dimly lit by a single, swaying bulb. It’s</p><p class=\"action\">colder here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(softly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This isn’t on the map.</p><p class=\"action\">He steps inside.</p><p class=\"action\">The air feels thick, pressing against his skin. He wipes his</p><p class=\"action\">arm. Damp.</p><p class=\"action\">A circular chalky pattern is drawn across the floor. Faded</p><p class=\"action\">symbols. Burn marks spiderweb out from the center.</p><p class=\"action\">Melted candles. Torn fabric. Scratched letters in the tile:</p><p class=\"character\">S-H-E-W-A-I-T-S.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(reads)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">\"She waits.\" Who waits?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You weren’t supposed to see this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">yet.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin spins, startled. Regan leans against the door frame,</p><p class=\"action\">arms folded.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Though, I should’ve guessed you'd</p><p class=\"dialogue\">wander. You’ve got that look.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What look?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The kind that doesn’t sit still</p><p class=\"dialogue\">when things feel wrong. The kind</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that breaks stuff to see what’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">inside.</p><p class=\"action\">She walks toward the symbol, barefoot. Calm. Like it doesn’t</p><p class=\"action\">scare her anymore.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is this?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">A game. A connection. Maybe both.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or maybe it’s nothing. Just our</p><p class=\"dialogue\">minds playing telephone with</p><p class=\"dialogue\">ghosts.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Who are you trying to talk to?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don't really care, I just try to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">see if something talks back.</p><p class=\"action\">She kneels and traces the edges of the circle with her</p><p class=\"action\">finger.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some say it answers yes or no</p><p class=\"dialogue\">questions. Others say it just</p><p class=\"dialogue\">listens. Otto says it rewinds time,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">but only for the wrong people. I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">have no idea what he’s talking</p><p class=\"dialogue\">about half the time.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You believe that?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I believe this place is a wound</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that won't heal.</p><p class=\"action\">Beat.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This whole place is infected.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why hasn’t anyone shut it down?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Health inspectors need to come in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Because some of us keep playing.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Even when we know better. Someone</p><p class=\"dialogue\">is funding this. I guess.</p><p class=\"action\">The temperature drops. Benjamin’s breath fogs. A low hum</p><p class=\"action\">begins, deep and vibrating.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you feel that?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah. Pressure. Cold.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I feel watched.</p><p class=\"action\">She looks up at him.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Feels like someone is always</p><p class=\"dialogue\">watching.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. GROUP ROOM – NEXT DAY</p><p class=\"action\">The circle is smaller today. Otto twitches. Carmilla stares</p><p class=\"action\">at her hands. Amber hums to her stuffed cat. Jace sits near</p><p class=\"action\">the wall, silent.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What did you do last night,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Found a room. There were symbols.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And how did it feel?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like I was watching someone else's</p><p class=\"dialogue\">dream.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(snaps)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are you drugging us? Why can’t I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">think straight?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not the first to say that.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How long has this been going on?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is this place?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not what. When.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(cutting in)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not asking the right</p><p class=\"dialogue\">questions. This isn’t therapy. It’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">containment.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(smiles gently)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think we’re all a little tired.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’ll pick this up tomorrow.</p><p class=\"action\">She scribbles something on her notepad, stands.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Be kind to each other. Goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">She leaves too quickly. The air feels like it’s holding its</p><p class=\"action\">breath.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(from the back)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They always bail when it gets real.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m done playing nice. I want</p><p class=\"dialogue\">answers.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then stop asking questions like a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">patient.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. BENJAMIN’S ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin sits cross-legged on the floor. Crumpled papers</p><p class=\"action\">surround him.</p><p class=\"action\">Drawings of the symbols, the circle, the S-H-E-W-A-I-T-S</p><p class=\"action\">inscription.</p><p class=\"action\">Diagrams, arrows, scribbled timelines. He’s trying to map the</p><p class=\"action\">madness.</p><p class=\"action\">His hands shake.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (TO HIMSELF)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This isn’t just therapy.</p><p class=\"action\">He draws a jagged line through the page, crossing out the</p><p class=\"action\">lie.</p><p class=\"character\">EXTENSION — INT. BENJAMIN’S ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Papers now blanket the bed, the floor, the desk. Symbols loop and</p><p class=\"dialogue\">overlap. Notes become paranoid fragments:</p><p class=\"action\">(cid:0) \"Too clean.\"</p><p class=\"action\">(cid:0) \"Mirrors?\"</p><p class=\"action\">(cid:0) \"Not healing. Holding.\"</p><p class=\"action\">(cid:0) \"Ask the girl?\"</p><p class=\"action\">(cid:0) \"Who is she and what is she waiting for?\"</p><p class=\"action\">He stares at the crude sketch of Dr. Anna’s face. Her smile too</p><p class=\"action\">perfect. Her eyes too distant.</p><p class=\"character\">A KNOCK.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The door opens with a gentle click.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello, Benjamin.</p><p class=\"action\">She steps inside. No clipboard. No folder.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t ask for a session.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I know. I felt invited.</p><p class=\"action\">She says it like she heard it whispered.</p><p class=\"action\">She sits, cross-legged, on the floor across from him.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you believe in messages from the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">beyond?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I believe something’s wrong with this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Would you like to talk to someone?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Talk to who? Isn’t that what you’re</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here for?</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That depends on the question. I can't</p><p class=\"dialogue\">answer your questions. I wasn't there.</p><p class=\"action\">She places her hand gently on the floor between them. Like she’s</p><p class=\"action\">waiting for something.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin hesitates.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What do you want from me?</p><p class=\"action\">A long silence. Then, softly,</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I just wanted to check on you.</p><p class=\"action\">She stands.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’ll talk again. When you're ready.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">She exits, leaving the candle flickering.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. UNUSED HALLWAY – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin wanders the dim corridor outside his room. Walls feel</p><p class=\"action\">like they’re pulsing. Distant whispers hum beneath the</p><p class=\"action\">fluorescents.</p><p class=\"action\">He turns a corner, nearly crashes into JACE, who leans against a</p><p class=\"action\">door frame, smoking something unlit.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You ever hear of personal space?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are you following me?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. You’re finally walking in the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">right direction.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin looks at him. Tired. Paranoid. More alert than before.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is she?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Depends on whose asking.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pauses)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If you mean the doctor, she’s a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">puppet. Or a radio. Or something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">worse.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She said she was invited.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So were we. Doesn’t mean we RSVP’d.</p><p class=\"action\">He opens the door beside him. A dark, dusty storage room with</p><p class=\"action\">tallies scratched deep into the walls.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ve been counting the days. But I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">think time here loops.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some of these marks were already here</p><p class=\"dialogue\">before I made them.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin looks down. One tally is different. Burned in, not</p><p class=\"action\">scratched.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You ever try to leave?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah. Once. Woke up right back in my</p><p class=\"dialogue\">bed. Except my bed wasn’t in my room</p><p class=\"dialogue\">anymore.</p><p class=\"action\">A beat.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Stick with Regan. Watch Amber. Avoid</p><p class=\"dialogue\">mirrors. And don’t trust the doctor.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s not very good at her job.</p><p class=\"action\">He walks away.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stays. One hand on the burned tally.</p><p class=\"action\">Then a whipser.</p><p class=\"character\">WHISPER (V.O.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello?</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 7</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. REGAN’S ROOM – DAY</p><p class=\"action\">Soft daylight glows through slatted blinds. This room, unlike</p><p class=\"action\">any other in the ward, feels human.</p><p class=\"action\">Hand-drawn sketches cover the walls, some hopeful, some</p><p class=\"action\">frantic. A line of paper cranes hangs like prayer flags. A</p><p class=\"action\">small plant, barely alive, clings to a plastic cup on the</p><p class=\"action\">windowsill.</p><p class=\"action\">A hand-lettered sign above the bed reads: “Hope lives here.”</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN and REGAN sit side-by-side on the narrow bed. Legs</p><p class=\"action\">almost touching. Silent, for once.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You made all this?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Keeps me sane. I used to draw</p><p class=\"dialogue\">before things stopped being</p><p class=\"dialogue\">manageable.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What happened?</p><p class=\"action\">She doesn't answer immediately. Instead, she pulls at a loose</p><p class=\"action\">thread in the blanket.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I thought if I kept people</p><p class=\"dialogue\">laughing, they wouldn’t see how</p><p class=\"dialogue\">broken I was. Pretending gets</p><p class=\"dialogue\">heavy. Eventually, it cracked</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something open.</p><p class=\"action\">She taps her temple. Then picks up a paper crane, turning it</p><p class=\"action\">delicately in her fingers.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They said it was a suicide attempt.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I said it was an accident.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe it was both.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I get that.</p><p class=\"action\">They sit in silence, but it's not awkward.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sometimes I wonder if anyone’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">really coming for us. Family.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Friends. The outside.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ve asked. They always point me to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Anna.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Always smiling. Always calm.Have</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you noticed she never answers</p><p class=\"dialogue\">directly? And she never lets you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">say goodbye first.</p><p class=\"action\">That lands heavy.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like a script.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah.</p><p class=\"action\">She reaches up, pulls down a paper crane.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Take it. Sometimes it's nice to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">have something real to hold onto.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin takes it carefully, like it might collapse in his</p><p class=\"action\">hands.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Thanks.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not alone here, Benjamin.</p><p class=\"action\">He smiles, barely. And it’s the first real one.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN enters to find OTTO near the window, wearing a</p><p class=\"action\">weathered military coat and “polishing” imaginary medals on</p><p class=\"action\">his chest with a handkerchief made of gauze.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You're late for debriefing. The</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Kaiser’s spies are in the vents.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t pretend you haven’t heard</p><p class=\"dialogue\">them.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think that’s the air system.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s what they want you to think.</p><p class=\"action\">A SMALL FIGURE sits cross-legged on the floor in the far</p><p class=\"action\">corner. Still as stone. Watching.</p><p class=\"action\">A boy. Maybe fifteen, but small for his age. Dark curls. Pale</p><p class=\"action\">skin. Slight build. Barefoot. He stares directly at Benjamin</p><p class=\"action\">with quiet intensity.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quietly, to Otto)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Who’s the kid?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(doesn’t look)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Little menace is what he is.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin turns his attention back to Otto.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So, Otto... what year is it?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">1917. If we don’t reinforce the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">east corridor by dawn, we’re</p><p class=\"dialogue\">compromised.</p><p class=\"action\">He lifts an invisible field radio to his mouth.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Copy that. I have eyes on the new</p><p class=\"dialogue\">recruit. He looks soft, but he’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">got potential.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin raises an eyebrow amused, a little unnerved.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He’s not soft. Just unbaked.</p><p class=\"action\">AMBER enters, holding her twine-wrapped cat like it’s</p><p class=\"action\">breathing.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto’s harmless. He’s just tuned to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a different channel. Or maybe a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">different timeline. I haven’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">decided.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m not tuned. I’m stationed.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever helps you cope, soldier.</p><p class=\"action\">She plops down beside Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He might’ve been here the longest.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or time just loops for him. Like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">VHS rewind.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Does anyone ever leave?</p><p class=\"action\">Otto and Amber exchange a glance.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Only in pieces.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or shadows. Depends on how much you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">remember.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re both incredibly comforting.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This pudding is definitely sentient.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s why you have to eat it fast.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Before it grows legs.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I confiscated a meatball last week.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It's under surveillance.</p><p class=\"action\">They all laugh genuinely. For a brief moment, it feels like</p><p class=\"action\">normalcy.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quietly, to Regan)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How do you make this bearable?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You don’t.</p><p class=\"action\">He nods, grateful. She nudges her tray toward him.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Also, bribe people with pudding.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly, the overhead lights flicker once, twice, then snap to</p><p class=\"action\">black for a split second.</p><p class=\"action\">When they return, everything is where it was. Except Amber’s cat</p><p class=\"action\">is gone from the table.</p><p class=\"action\">She freezes. Looks down at her hands, then under the table.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He was right here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You sure?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t lose him. He doesn’t leave.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone quiets.</p><p class=\"action\">From across the cafeteria, Jace watches them. Leaning against the</p><p class=\"action\">wall.</p><p class=\"action\">He tilts his head slightly then, walks away.</p><p class=\"action\">Cut to Malachai sitting in the floor. In his lap is Amber's</p><p class=\"action\">stuffed cat.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He wanted to see the hallway. I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">took him for a walk.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What the hell?</p><p class=\"action\">Amber storms in and sees the cat. Freezes.</p><p class=\"action\">MALACHAI holds it out with both hands, like an offering.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He was lonely. He told me so.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber snatches the cat — quickly checks it. It’s unharmed,</p><p class=\"action\">but now wrapped in red thread, tied in precise loops.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You don’t get to touch him.</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai SCREAMS.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone jolts. Then silence.</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai tilts his head slightly.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are you listening? She is.</p><p class=\"action\">He stands. Walks away, barefoot. Whispers something to the</p><p class=\"action\">wall as he passes it.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin turns to Otto.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is wrong with him?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO(HUSHED)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some say he’s been here longer than</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the floorboards.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But, he's just a kid.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin watches Malachai disappear around the corner.</p><p class=\"action\">CUT TO: Amber clutching her cat, unsettled.</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 8</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ANNA’S OFFICE – EVENING</p><p class=\"action\">The room glows with flickering amber light. Anna moves like</p><p class=\"action\">she’s following choreography only she can hear. Deliberate.</p><p class=\"action\">Silent. Sacred.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin sits rigid in a high-backed chair across from her.</p><p class=\"action\">His fingers dig into the carved arms of the seat. Symbols</p><p class=\"action\">etched into the wood glow faintly when touched.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You always say hello. Never hi.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Never hey. You don’t have to be so</p><p class=\"dialogue\">formal. We’re all crazy here.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Words matter.</p><p class=\"action\">She lights another candle, gaze unbroken.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Tell me how you have been since you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">arrived.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Uneasy. Feels like there’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something in the walls. A noise</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that isn’t just pipes or vents.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And what do you believe that noise</p><p class=\"dialogue\">means?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I believe it means I’m not alone</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here. Really not alone. Other than</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the other crazies.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So, is that what this is? Just a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">bunch of feelings?</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. It’s a place where your mind</p><p class=\"dialogue\">shows you what it avoids. Where</p><p class=\"dialogue\">healing begins.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t need riddles. I need</p><p class=\"dialogue\">answers. I want to talk to my</p><p class=\"dialogue\">sister. I want to leave.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t decide that.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s not an answer. What does</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that even mean?? You really aren’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">very good at this.</p><p class=\"action\">She smiles. Vague.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Okay, Benjamin. Goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">The candle beside Benjamin extinguishes itself.</p><p class=\"action\">A beat of silence.</p><p class=\"action\">He stands, eyes darting toward the door.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s it?</p><p class=\"action\">No answer. Anna just stares. And then turns her head</p><p class=\"action\">slightly, as if hearing a voice no one else does.</p><p class=\"action\">Her lips move soundlessly. Then</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (SOFTLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Someone new is listening.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY OUTSIDE THE OFFICE – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin exits, rattled. The hallway is dark. Unusually so.</p><p class=\"action\">Whispers echo faintly. Not words. Just tones. He turns. No</p><p class=\"action\">one there.</p><p class=\"action\">He picks up his pace. Passing one door at a time. The doors</p><p class=\"action\">are marked A, B, C, D.</p><p class=\"action\">Then stops. At the end of the hallway, Lucy stands. Still.</p><p class=\"action\">Watching.</p><p class=\"action\">She takes a step forward.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hey. Are you okay?</p><p class=\"action\">No answer.</p><p class=\"action\">She raises one hand. Her palm is covered in black marker. A</p><p class=\"action\">symbol matching the one carved into Anna’s desk.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You weren’t supposed to say</p><p class=\"dialogue\">goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">Her voice is delicate. Almost childlike.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What?</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She was still talking.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin turns to look behind him. The hallway is now</p><p class=\"action\">completely empty.</p><p class=\"action\">When he turns back, Lucy is gone.</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 6</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. AMBER’S ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Amber’s room is dim and strange. Childhood clutter mixed with</p><p class=\"action\">neglect. Tattered lace curtains flutter, though the window is</p><p class=\"action\">closed.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber sits cross-legged on the floor. The twine cat rests in</p><p class=\"action\">her lap.</p><p class=\"action\">A soft knock.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hey. Regan said I’d find you here.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And look at that. You did.</p><p class=\"action\">He lingers in the doorway.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She said you might know something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">about the noises. About this place.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Is it haunted? I know that sounds</p><p class=\"dialogue\">crazy.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber pats the floor beside her.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sit. Quiet now. They listen through</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the vents.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin lowers himself beside her, careful not to crush a</p><p class=\"action\">drawing of a spiral made of teeth.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ve been here longer than some. I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">used to think it was a dream. But I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">remember things now.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Remember what?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How easy it is to disappear.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m sure your family hasn’t—</p><p class=\"action\">She cuts him off with a look. Her eyes shimmer, then harden.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. Maybe they’re ashamed. There</p><p class=\"dialogue\">are doors here. Ones that aren’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">meant to open. But I found one.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How do you know that?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin raises an eyebrow. Skeptical.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Because everything feels wrong near</p><p class=\"dialogue\">them. And it smells funny. I swear</p><p class=\"dialogue\">they pump pot through the vents to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">keep us chill.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin chuckles.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And you still went close?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t mean to. I just stopped</p><p class=\"dialogue\">there one day. And it felt like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">standing too close to something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hot.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did it open?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No.</p><p class=\"action\">A low hum starts in the walls. Subtle at first. Then louder.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber closes her eyes and tilts her head. Listening.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It's shifting again.</p><p class=\"action\">She presses her palm to the floor.</p><p class=\"action\">The humming deepens for a moment, like the room reacts.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Tomorrow, I’ll show you something.</p><p class=\"action\">She looks directly at him. No smile. No twitch.</p><p class=\"action\">Just the weight of certainty.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. OUTDOOR COURTYARD – DAY</p><p class=\"action\">A rare patch of sunlight spills into a stone-walled</p><p class=\"action\">courtyard. Weeds burst through cracks in the concrete. It's</p><p class=\"action\">the only place that feels alive.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan and Benjamin sit on a weathered bench. A breeze moves</p><p class=\"action\">through her curls.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I used to think I was unlovable.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin pauses.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s easy to say that. But when you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hate your own reflection.</p><p class=\"action\">She breathes deeply. Watches a butterfly land on her knee,</p><p class=\"action\">then fly away.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I never expected to find a friend</p><p class=\"dialogue\">in here. Someone who makes it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">easier.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re the only reason I haven’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">completely lost it.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Look around.</p><p class=\"action\">They both laugh, but it’s tired.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sometimes I imagine walking out of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here and not feeling watched.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah? What would your first outing</p><p class=\"dialogue\">be as a free woman?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’d walk into a diner. Order</p><p class=\"dialogue\">waffles. And not apologize for</p><p class=\"dialogue\">wanting extra syrup.</p><p class=\"action\">They both chuckle, a real moment of levity.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you think it’s possible, really</p><p class=\"dialogue\">possible, to ever leave this place?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why not? We didn’t hurt anyone.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe we get better. Maybe we</p><p class=\"dialogue\">don’t. But we won’t stay forever.</p><p class=\"action\">She rests her head on his shoulder.</p><p class=\"action\">They sit in quiet.</p><p class=\"action\">Then, something moves across the edge of the courtyard. Just</p><p class=\"action\">behind the hedge wall. A shadow, too tall to be human, slips</p><p class=\"action\">out of view.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin lifts his head.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did you see that?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">See what?</p><p class=\"action\">He stares for a moment longer.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Never mind.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan shifts closer, eyes closed.</p><p class=\"action\">A crumpled paper crane blows across the concrete and stops at</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin’s foot, as if placed there.</p><p class=\"character\">CONTINUED – INT. SERVICE CORRIDOR – NIGHT</p><p class=\"dialogue\">DIM. NARROW. INDUSTRIAL.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin follows Amber and Regan down a hallway lined with storage</p><p class=\"action\">doors and utility panels. This part of the building feels older,</p><p class=\"action\">like it wasn’t built with the rest of the hospital.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are we even allowed down here?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are we allowed anywhere? Doesn’t stop</p><p class=\"dialogue\">them from watching.</p><p class=\"action\">She stops abruptly in front of a steel utility door with no knob,</p><p class=\"action\">just a flat plate of metal and an uneven seam.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This wasn’t always here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What do you mean?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ve walked this hall a hundred times.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">One day, boom. It’s just here.</p><p class=\"action\">She kneels. Runs her fingers along the floor in front of it.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Feel this?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin kneels and touches the tile and shivers. The air near the</p><p class=\"action\">door is cold, like standing next to a freezer that hums. Almost</p><p class=\"action\">alive.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">People say it’s where the ones who</p><p class=\"dialogue\">vanish go.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You believe that? That makes no sense.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (SARCASM)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah, they're just storing bodies</p><p class=\"dialogue\">in a closet.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I just listen to others. I'm not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">saying it's true.</p><p class=\"action\">She takes a twine bracelet off her wrist and lays it on the floor</p><p class=\"action\">in front of the door.</p><p class=\"action\">They all wait.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What are you do-</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Shh!</p><p class=\"action\">For a long, terrible second nothing.</p><p class=\"action\">The bracelet slides forward on its own, as if pulled.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Jesus!</p><p class=\"action\">Amber whispers, eyes locked on the seam:</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s listening to us.</p><p class=\"action\">A faint, high-pitched ringing starts in their ears.</p><p class=\"character\">A DEEP KNOCK.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">From the other side of the door.</p><p class=\"action\">Three slow, deliberate thuds. Benjamin stumbles back.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Nope. No. We’re not doing this.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What the hell? Why have you never</p><p class=\"dialogue\">showed me this?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I told you I’d show you something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">real, Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(To Regan)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Because you never asked.</p><p class=\"action\">She picks up the bracelet and pockets it calmly.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They don’t like being ignored.</p><p class=\"action\">She turns and walks down the hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stays frozen — staring at the door.</p><p class=\"action\">Behind him, faint scratching sounds echo from the seam.</p><p class=\"shot\">Scene 10</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ANNA’S OFFICE - NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin sits in the velvet chair once again. A dense fog of</p><p class=\"action\">sage smoke coils through the dim room. A circle of crystals</p><p class=\"action\">surrounds a small candle that flickers erratically.</p><p class=\"action\">The air feels warmer than it should.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna enters without a sound.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why are you always burning</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something?</p><p class=\"action\">He waves his hand through the smoke, irritated.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You realize it reeks, right?</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Focus. Boundaries.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The same reason I ask questions. To</p><p class=\"dialogue\">make you look inward.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You ever try answering any?</p><p class=\"action\">Anna sits slowly. Between them, a small hourglass filled with</p><p class=\"action\">black sand. She flips it. Begins writing something in her</p><p class=\"action\">leather-bound notebook.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you rest? Are you comfortable?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I keep having vivid dreams. Symbols</p><p class=\"dialogue\">everywhere. A circle. A line</p><p class=\"dialogue\">through it. Rooms that twist and</p><p class=\"dialogue\">turn. I think this place is messing</p><p class=\"dialogue\">with me.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">People use symbols when they can’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">say things out loud.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I need more than riddles.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I can’t answer your questions,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin. I wasn’t there.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin leans forward, jaw tight, eyes sharp.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Stop talking like a fortune cookie.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(slams palm on the desk)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Tell me why the walls make noise.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why Amber says we’re not supposed</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to be here.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna looks up. Not startled. Just still.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know why you’re here. I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">really don’t.</p><p class=\"action\">She lights another stick of incense. Murmurs a phrase under</p><p class=\"action\">her breath, syllables that don’t belong to any recognizable</p><p class=\"action\">language.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin’s eyes narrow.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Because some places are built to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hold, not to heal. Some places</p><p class=\"dialogue\">aren’t meant to fix people.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So we’re prisoners?</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You are free to leave whenever you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">would like.</p><p class=\"action\">She stands.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I have to run.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">She turns her back.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. Not this time. You’re saying I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">can leave? I’m not being held here?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Answer me.</p><p class=\"action\">He grabs the hourglass from the table, lifts it, and hurls it</p><p class=\"action\">against the wall.</p><p class=\"character\">CRASH.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Black sand spills across the floor.</p><p class=\"action\">The flame on the candle flashes BLUE, then PURPLE.</p><p class=\"action\">The flame on the candle flashes blue, then purple. The smoke</p><p class=\"action\">halts, suspended in midair.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Answer me!</p><p class=\"action\">He rushes to the door. When he throws it open, he doesn't</p><p class=\"action\">find the hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">Instead, a mirror version of the office. The same chair. The</p><p class=\"action\">same symbols. Empty. A flicker of movement. A reflection of</p><p class=\"action\">himself seated calmly in the chair. But it’s not him. It’s</p><p class=\"action\">still.</p><p class=\"action\">He slams the door shut again.</p><p class=\"action\">The real office now looks faded. Wrong. Like a bad copy.</p><p class=\"action\">The candle now burns blue. The wax runs in unnatural</p><p class=\"action\">directions, sideways, upward.</p><p class=\"action\">On the desk, in place of the hourglass: A new drawing.</p><p class=\"action\">A circle with a line through it, scrawled in wax like a child</p><p class=\"action\">did it.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stares at it, breath quickening.</p><p class=\"action\">A sound behind him.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You cracked it.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin turns. Lucy stands in the corner of the room,</p><p class=\"action\">silent, pale, fingers dripping wax. Eyes unreadable.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But you’re not ready for what’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">inside.</p><p class=\"action\">She vanishes as if she was never there.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin’s breath catches.</p><p class=\"action\">He slowly sinks into the velvet chair. Stares at the symbol</p><p class=\"action\">on the desk, burned into the wood like it was always there.</p><p class=\"action\">He laughs once, bitter and hollow. Then presses both hands to</p><p class=\"action\">his face.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (QUIETLY, TO HIMSELF)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know what’s real anymore. I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">don’t know where I am. I need to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">speak to my family.</p><p class=\"action\">Tears slip through his fingers, silent.</p><p class=\"action\">He looks toward the empty doorway where Anna disappeared and</p><p class=\"action\">speaks softly, broken:</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please. Just tell me the truth.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Even if it kills me.</p><p class=\"action\">Nothing.</p><p class=\"action\">Just the drip of wax and the low hum in the walls.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 11</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. EAST WING – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Amber leads Benjamin and Regan down a long-forgotten hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">Dust hangs in the air. The walls pulse faintly.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No one’s supposed to know this is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You really do know a lot about this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place. Why haven't you figured out</p><p class=\"dialogue\">how to leave yet?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I just assumed I had to do my time.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever that means.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why are you even here?</p><p class=\"action\">Amber pauses. Looking ahead as if trying to remember.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She doesn’t know. I’ve asked her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">before.</p><p class=\"action\">She pushes aside a tall, grimy chalkboard. Behind it, nearly</p><p class=\"action\">consumed by shadow, is a door with no handle.</p><p class=\"action\">It groans open.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HIDDEN RECORD ROOM – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Rows of rusted metal shelves. Mold-blackened files. Cassette</p><p class=\"action\">tapes, unlabeled, some warped from time. A cracked intercom</p><p class=\"action\">speaker hisses softly.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This looks like patient records.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The kind they don’t want shared.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin runs his fingers across the dusty labels. Stops.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is mine.</p><p class=\"action\">He pulls the folder. Nearly every line is redacted.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This makes no sense.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some of them are fake. Yours</p><p class=\"dialogue\">doesn’t look like it. That’s why</p><p class=\"dialogue\">they keep watching you.</p><p class=\"action\">A sudden gasp from Regan.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is that?</p><p class=\"action\">In the corner, behind discarded linens and rusted stools, a</p><p class=\"action\">trapdoor half-covered by a tarp.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">A basement?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh, I'm going in.</p><p class=\"action\">The humming returns, louder here. Pressure builds in the</p><p class=\"action\">walls.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber places a hand on the trapdoor, eyes fluttering closed.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever’s down there, it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">probably worse than the rest of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">this place.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You and the creepy shit.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’re already too far in not to.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Besides, what else do we have to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">do? Finger paint?</p><p class=\"action\">He kneels and lifts the trapdoor.</p><p class=\"action\">A burst of cold air hits them. The scent of wet stone and</p><p class=\"action\">something forgotten.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. TRAPDOOR CHAMBER – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The three descend narrow, creaking stairs. Only Regan’s</p><p class=\"action\">flashlight lights the way, flickering.</p><p class=\"action\">They enter a chamber that shouldn’t exist. Carved stone</p><p class=\"action\">instead of cement. Uneven.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This place gives me chills.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It doesn’t feel like a basement. It</p><p class=\"dialogue\">feels wrong.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s not a basement. It’s older.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This was here before the hospital.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I swear to god if I find out this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place was built on an ancient</p><p class=\"dialogue\">burial ground!</p><p class=\"action\">They move deeper, stepping over cracked tiles etched with</p><p class=\"action\">symbols. Cobwebs cling to the walls. The air vibrates softly.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan stops.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Look at this.</p><p class=\"action\">A wall of tally marks. Hundreds, maybe thousands. Uneven.</p><p class=\"action\">Carved deep.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Someone kept count. Did Jace do</p><p class=\"dialogue\">this?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Of what? Days here? Days until he</p><p class=\"dialogue\">leaves?</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly the flashlight dies.</p><p class=\"action\">Complete darkness. Amber trips and falls.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Amber? Regan?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m here. I'm on the floor, but I’m</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Something’s in here with us.</p><p class=\"action\">A sound brushes past them. Like breathing, but wrong. Then</p><p class=\"action\">silence.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin’s hand brushes the wall. It pulses beneath his</p><p class=\"action\">fingers.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let’s go back. NOW!</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Wait. What is this?</p><p class=\"action\">She feels along the floor. Her hand closes around a small</p><p class=\"action\">rusted tin box.</p><p class=\"action\">Inside: old Polaroids (faces scratched out), a small</p><p class=\"action\">porcelain doll, and a strange carved object; wooden, oblong.</p><p class=\"action\">They all freeze.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why would this be down here?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to show the others.</p><p class=\"action\">As they move toward the stairs, a sound fills the chamber.</p><p class=\"action\">Not a voice.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber clutches the box tighter as the run back upstairs.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. EAST WING – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">They emerge breathless. Benjamin looks back one last time.</p><p class=\"action\">The trapdoor is closed. He didn't close it.</p><p class=\"action\">CONTINUED – INT. COMMON ROOM – LATER THAT NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The group is gathered in a semicircle: Amber, Benjamin, Regan,</p><p class=\"action\">Otto, Carmilla, and Jace, who leans against the wall, arms</p><p class=\"action\">crossed.</p><p class=\"action\">The rusted tin box sits on the table. The objects inside are laid</p><p class=\"action\">out: Polaroids, the doll, and the glass-eyed wooden artifact.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is a ritual box.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We found it in a chamber under the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">East Wing. A place that’s not even on</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the map.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s older than the hospital. There</p><p class=\"dialogue\">were symbols. Walls covered in tally</p><p class=\"dialogue\">marks. Someone was counting something.</p><p class=\"action\">They all look at Jace.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don't look at me. I'm not going</p><p class=\"dialogue\">down there.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Tally marks aren’t always days.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sometimes they’re debts.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You should’ve left it there.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did you know about it?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No, but I know enough to leave sealed</p><p class=\"dialogue\">things sealed.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is it?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Memory. In pieces. Something they</p><p class=\"dialogue\">tried to get rid of. Or forget.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Someone did not want it found, that's</p><p class=\"dialogue\">for sure.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(sharply)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Forget what? That we’re being kept</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here? That this place doesn’t make</p><p class=\"dialogue\">sense?</p><p class=\"action\">He slams a hand on the table. Everyone flinches.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Can someone rein in the crazy for two</p><p class=\"dialogue\">minutes? Anyone? Just stop talking</p><p class=\"dialogue\">around it. I want the truth.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re in the wrong place for that,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Price.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Truth’s a dangerous thing in a locked</p><p class=\"dialogue\">ward.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Especially one that lost its key.</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla sips the tea she always seems to have.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin takes an annoyed breath. His eyes flick to Regan, who’s</p><p class=\"action\">watching him.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We can’t stay passive anymore. Not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">after that.</p><p class=\"action\">He looks at the box, his hands trembling.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We found something. We can’t just</p><p class=\"dialogue\">pretend we didn’t.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No one’s pretending. But you have to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">understand.</p><p class=\"action\">She looks around. Voice lowering.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whoever’s watching saw us down there.</p><p class=\"action\">A long beat.</p><p class=\"action\">Lucy appears in the doorway.</p><p class=\"action\">Still. Barefoot. Eyes unreadable.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone turns toward her. No one speaks.</p><p class=\"action\">She steps into the room, silent. Reaches toward the Polaroids then</p><p class=\"action\">stops.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You won’t like what’s missing.</p><p class=\"action\">She turns, walks away.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(under his breath)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Of course she shows up now.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What did she mean?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe not everything in that box came</p><p class=\"dialogue\">back with you.</p><p class=\"action\">Without warning, MALACHAI launches himself at Benjamin’s</p><p class=\"action\">back. Arms and legs wrap around him. The room gasps.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">(whispers in Benjamin’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">ear)</p><p class=\"action\">Maybe it's me. Maybe I did it.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Get off me, you fucking spider</p><p class=\"dialogue\">monkey!</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai lets go and scurries under a table.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Jesus Christ. Someone put a leash</p><p class=\"dialogue\">on that kid.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 12</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – DAY</p><p class=\"action\">A heavy silence. Dim light filters through stained-glass panels</p><p class=\"action\">that didn’t exist yesterday.</p><p class=\"action\">The group sits in a loose circle: Benjamin, Amber, Regan, Otto,</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla, and now, a new presence.</p><p class=\"action\">HAROLD (60s), white button-down stained with ink, suspenders</p><p class=\"action\">twisted, a large notebook filled with chaotic diagrams in his</p><p class=\"action\">lap. He mutters quietly to himself as he draws overlapping</p><p class=\"action\">circles.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin sets the rusted tin box on the table. The others lean in.</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai is hanging upside down from a pipe, legs hooked,</p><p class=\"action\">arms dangling, staring directly at Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(mutters, crossing himself)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Saint Michael defend us.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">(gripping her rosary, dances</p><p class=\"dialogue\">around)</p><p class=\"action\">It’s awake.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin points to his eyes, then back at Malachai as if to</p><p class=\"action\">say \"I'm watching you.\"</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai hisses as Benjamin pulls his attention back to the</p><p class=\"action\">others.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This was underneath the East Wing.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Buried. Behind a false wall. Beneath a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">trapdoor.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It wasn’t just dust and old files.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There was something down there.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We heard shit. I felt watched.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(scribbling)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Old frequencies. Not language.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Something repeating.</p><p class=\"action\">They turn to him.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Who are you again?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold. I draw things so I don’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">forget them.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pauses, then solemnly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I saw this box in a dream once. Except</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it was made of metal.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That... tracks.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly, the door creaks open.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna enters, unnervingly serene. Her footsteps make no sound.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello. Good morning.</p><p class=\"action\">She spots the box instantly. Her expression flickers, then resets.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What have you been up to?</p><p class=\"action\">She approaches, peers inside. Her fingers graze the carved object.</p><p class=\"action\">The room dims. Light bulbs flicker.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(whispers)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The flame dipped. And there’s no</p><p class=\"dialogue\">flame.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Have you been busy?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We found this. In a locked chamber</p><p class=\"dialogue\">under the foundation of this place.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t like this.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You knew it was there. You let us</p><p class=\"dialogue\">wander into it.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I told you, some questions I can’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">answer.</p><p class=\"action\">She closes the box slowly and lifts it beneath her arm like</p><p class=\"action\">something precious.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Well, can you answer ONE question?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is YOUR job.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please don’t push this.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know what’s down there.</p><p class=\"action\">She turns. Fearful.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This session is over.</p><p class=\"action\">A long pause.</p><p class=\"action\">Then:</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">She exits. The room holds its breath.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did anyone else feel that?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like air was sucked out of the room.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever that is, I want nothing to do</p><p class=\"dialogue\">with it. It feels wrong.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Time jumped when she touched it. Did</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you feel that gap?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s hiding something. Whatever this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">is, it’s not just a hospital..</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What does it want?</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(giggles)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(whispers)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">To keep us.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It doesn’t let things finish.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold doesn't look up, continues drawing.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin drops his head onto the desk, frustrated.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan pats him on the back.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There there.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We shouldn’t push further.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But we’re in it. We’re already in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">whatever this is.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He stares at the door where Anna vanished.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And we’re still part of it. Like it or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">not.</p><p class=\"character\">CONTINUED – INT. COMMON ROOM – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin continues staring at the door.</p><p class=\"action\">The others are quiet.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold hasn’t moved. He draws faster now. Wild arcs, tall shadow</p><p class=\"action\">figures next to stick people with crossed-out faces.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(tapping the paper)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s always the same. The tall ones</p><p class=\"dialogue\">come when things get too close. The</p><p class=\"dialogue\">door opens wrong.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What door?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not like a normal door. It opens</p><p class=\"dialogue\">wrong.</p><p class=\"action\">He flips the page. Points to a rough sketch of the common room.</p><p class=\"action\">The chairs are drawn upside down.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ve been here before. But I hadn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">arrived yet.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold, what does that mean?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It means I should have left. I don’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">know why I keep coming back.</p><p class=\"action\">A long silence.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You think we’re next?</p><p class=\"action\">Harold slowly looks up at him. For a rare moment, his voice is</p><p class=\"action\">calm. Almost lucid.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not next.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re the reason the order breaks.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He doesn’t belong to it.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not yet. But he will.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(to Harold)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Okay, old man. Maybe take a breath.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I did. Didn't help.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin kneels next to him.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold... what are they trying to do to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">us?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not trying. Doing. You should</p><p class=\"dialogue\">interfere.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Doing what?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’re keeping us. For safekeeping.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They aren't healing us.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did anyone get meds today?</p><p class=\"action\">Harold stares ahead. Then returns to his drawing humming quietly</p><p class=\"action\">and off-key.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 13</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. REGAN’S ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Regan paces, chewing her thumbnail. Benjamin sits cross-legged on</p><p class=\"action\">her bed, flipping through one of Amber’s hand-drawn maps of the</p><p class=\"action\">facility.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She just left. Just like that. No</p><p class=\"dialogue\">explanation. No warning.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She knew it was there. That means</p><p class=\"dialogue\">she’s been lying to all of us.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not just lying. Hiding things.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber enters, breathless, holding a tattered book bound in red</p><p class=\"action\">twine.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She keeps records of every object she</p><p class=\"dialogue\">collects.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin opens it, pages filled with sketches of strange objects,</p><p class=\"action\">paired with patient initials and cryptic notes. The final page is</p><p class=\"action\">mostly blank, save for one line:</p><p class=\"action\">\"The medium doesn’t realize she is the channel.\"</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What does that mean?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You think one of us is a... medium?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly, the lights flicker. A sharp buzz hums from the vent</p><p class=\"action\">above.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s starting again.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to move it. If she feels</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something’s off, it’s only a matter of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">time before someone else stumbles onto</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And figure out what it is.</p><p class=\"action\">They exchange a glance, fear mixed with resolve.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And do what? Some old Polaroids aren't</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the answer to whatever the hell is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">going on.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. But it wasn’t hidden by</p><p class=\"dialogue\">accident.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – LATER THAT NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The group regathers. The room is dim, thunder rumbling beyond the</p><p class=\"action\">cracked windows.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto paces in the corner, agitated. Carmilla clutches her rosary</p><p class=\"action\">tighter than ever. Harold is sprawled on the floor with his</p><p class=\"action\">notebook, sketching rapidly.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We wait until Anna’s rounds are over.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then we go to her office.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If anyone’s watching, it’ll be quiet</p><p class=\"dialogue\">after rounds. That’s our window. I'm</p><p class=\"dialogue\">going to bed until this shit is over.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(tapping a page)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You open the wrong door... things come</p><p class=\"dialogue\">back wrong.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then we knock first.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. No! It’s a trap! The place lets</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you think you found something.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto—calm down.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You don’t get it! I saw what happened</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to the others who asked too many</p><p class=\"dialogue\">questions. They vanish!</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hush. Fear feeds what’s listening.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sometimes fear is the correct</p><p class=\"dialogue\">response.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto kicks over a chair.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone flinches. Even Harold stops drawing.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto, we’re on your side. We’re all</p><p class=\"dialogue\">trying to figure this out.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You weren’t here before. And it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">starting again.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You need to sit. Please.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto backs into the far corner. Eyes wide. Mumbles incoherently.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s inside the walls. Watching.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(softly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It listens, too.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to move. Now. Before this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place swallows another one of us.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let’s go.</p><p class=\"action\">They begin filing out — Amber, Regan, Carmilla, Harold trailing</p><p class=\"action\">behind, stuffing his notebook into his shirt.</p><p class=\"action\">As the exit the common room, find MALACHAI sitting in a</p><p class=\"action\">chalk-drawn circle of tally's, Y’s and N’s alternating around</p><p class=\"action\">the edge.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Wanna play? You ask, I answer. But</p><p class=\"dialogue\">no touching.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin steps closer.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Careful. If you lie in the circle,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it grabs you.</p><p class=\"action\">He taps his head.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s how I got stuck.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m really trying not to judge</p><p class=\"dialogue\">right now.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan grabs Benjamin's arm and leads him along.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Come on. Leave the wild child</p><p class=\"dialogue\">alone.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If you see the hallway double back</p><p class=\"dialogue\">on itself... run toward it. Not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">away.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto doesn’t answer. He rocks in place, whispering.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They are going to get us all killed...</p><p class=\"action\">He scratches at the wall with his fingernail.</p><p class=\"action\">The others disappear into the hallway. Thunder rolls louder.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto stops scratching. Looks at his finger. Blood.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 11</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY OUTSIDE ANNA’S OFFICE – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The group creeps through the dim corridor — Benjamin, Regan,</p><p class=\"action\">Amber, Carmilla, and Harold — silent but wide-eyed.</p><p class=\"action\">Lights flicker like they’re blinking. The floor creaks behind</p><p class=\"action\">them, though no one is there.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold jogs up from the far hallway, breathless, clutching</p><p class=\"action\">his notebook to his chest.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Wait. Don’t leave me behind this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">time.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There.</p><p class=\"action\">He points to the door marked DR. ANNA.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s locked.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I can pick it.</p><p class=\"action\">She kneels and produces a bent hairpin from inside her</p><p class=\"action\">sleeve. The others keep watch. Harold hums quietly, something</p><p class=\"action\">out of tune.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Well aren’t you the little</p><p class=\"dialogue\">criminal? Hurry. I don’t like this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hallway.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think it’s... longer than it was.</p><p class=\"action\">CLICK. The door opens.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ANNA’S OFFICE – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">The room is darker than before. Candles burn low, casting</p><p class=\"action\">warped shadows that seem to shift when no one moves.</p><p class=\"action\">Crystals vibrate softly on their shelves. Papers flutter even</p><p class=\"action\">without wind.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Check everything.</p><p class=\"action\">They scatter.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber pulls books from the shelf, flipping pages.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan opens a drawer; patient files, half-burned.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold stares at the ceiling, scribbling invisible symbols in</p><p class=\"action\">the air.</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla crosses herself and murmurs.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quietly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What's in here?</p><p class=\"action\">She lifts a loose floorboard beneath the woven rug. Nothing</p><p class=\"action\">underneath. No box. No object.</p><p class=\"action\">Just scuff marks.</p><p class=\"action\">Dust disturbed recently.</p><p class=\"action\">The faint outline where something used to sit.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s been opened.</p><p class=\"action\">He pulls it out. Inside: the photographs, the doll, but the</p><p class=\"action\">wooden object is gone.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Recently?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah. Not carefully, either.</p><p class=\"action\">She runs her fingers along the edge of the wood.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Someone didn’t want to leave it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or didn’t want us finding it here.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is she hiding?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin searches behind the desk and finds a journal, bound</p><p class=\"action\">in leather. He flips through it.</p><p class=\"action\">A low hum begins. Subtle. Almost electrical.</p><p class=\"action\">The candles tremble. Flames stretch unnaturally tall, then go</p><p class=\"action\">out.</p><p class=\"action\">Darkness.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(shaking)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’re watching. They’ve always</p><p class=\"dialogue\">watched. We stayed too long.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to go.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Wait—</p><p class=\"action\">A whisper, close to Benjamin’s ear. No breath. No voice.</p><p class=\"action\">Not words.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin flinches.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What did you feel?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like... something noticed I was</p><p class=\"dialogue\">looking.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone goes still.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold nods once.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’ll hear more now. That’s the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">cost of being here. That's how they</p><p class=\"dialogue\">drive you mad.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Well, Madder.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(thinks)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">More mad?</p><p class=\"action\">They move for the door.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">—And are met with a hallway that is no longer the same.</p><p class=\"action\">The floor appears longer, stretching ahead like a tunnel.</p><p class=\"action\">Doors shift slightly when stared at.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh God. It's shifting.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh god, what have we done?</p><p class=\"action\">They start running.</p><p class=\"action\">The further they move, the more warped the space becomes.</p><p class=\"action\">Paintings hang upside down, light bulbs flicker with whispers</p><p class=\"action\">instead of buzz, a door appears, then vanishes as they</p><p class=\"action\">approach.</p><p class=\"action\">They reach an intersection.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Wait—wait—don't go left.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Left is yesterday. If you go back,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you won't be you anymore.</p><p class=\"action\">For some reason this makes sense. They go right.</p><p class=\"action\">As they run, the lights behind them shatter one by one.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Keep going!</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where are we even going?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Anywhere but here!</p><p class=\"action\">As they round the final turn, the hallway abruptly snaps back</p><p class=\"action\">to normal; bright lights, soft hum of the vents.</p><p class=\"action\">Silence.</p><p class=\"action\">They stop, panting. No one speaks for a moment.</p><p class=\"action\">Then:</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Next time, it won’t reset. I've</p><p class=\"dialogue\">seen it.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It doesn't like it when we're</p><p class=\"dialogue\">naughty.</p><p class=\"action\">Camilla says sing-songy with a wild smile.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin slides down the wall, out of breath.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 15</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. LOWER CORRIDORS – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The corridor pulses with red light. The floor underfoot</p><p class=\"action\">breathes just slightly. Benjamin, Amber, Regan, and Harold</p><p class=\"action\">walk through the halls.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’re not in the same wing anymore.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This place... It’s rewriting</p><p class=\"dialogue\">itself.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is giving serious hell mouth</p><p class=\"dialogue\">vibes. Buffy would not be</p><p class=\"dialogue\">impressed.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Amber fist bump without looking at each other.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Nice.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(then)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to stay together. Keep</p><p class=\"dialogue\">moving.</p><p class=\"action\">They advance. Shadows move independently of them.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. WIDE CHAMBER – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">The group stops short.</p><p class=\"action\">At the center of the room, the floor is damaged.</p><p class=\"action\">Circles scratched over older circles. Lines cut through them</p><p class=\"action\">again and again. Not fresh, Layered.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This wasn’t done by one person.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or all at once. A low sound builds.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not a growl. Not a voice.</p><p class=\"action\">More like feedback. The shadows in the room misalign, lagging</p><p class=\"action\">behind their movements by half a second. Amber steps forward.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s not one of us.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Demon. That is 100% a demon.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is where people get stuck.</p><p class=\"action\">The sound spikes.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls flex inward; not collapsing, just correcting.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(panicked)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’re too close. It doesn’t like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">witnesses.</p><p class=\"action\">The floor shifts beneath them.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">MOVE!</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HIDDEN STAIRCASE – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">They slam through a broken archway into a narrow stone</p><p class=\"action\">stairwell. Dust and heat.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. UNDERGROUND CHAMBER – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">A wide circular room, candlelit. Every wall is carved with</p><p class=\"action\">symbols Amber once sketched.</p><p class=\"action\">Inside it, the wooden object rests, inert. Ordinary. Out of</p><p class=\"action\">place.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is where they practiced. Over</p><p class=\"dialogue\">and over. Until it worked.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe its an access point. Or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">summoning chamber.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So... weren't dropped here. We were</p><p class=\"dialogue\">placed here? And who the fuck is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">being summoned??</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think they’re bringing them here.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">On purpose. Maybe not the purpose</p><p class=\"dialogue\">they want you to think, but A</p><p class=\"dialogue\">purpose.</p><p class=\"action\">The door slams shut behind them. The hum returns louder.</p><p class=\"action\">Almost angry.</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla rocks gently, smiling at something only she sees</p><p class=\"action\">while dancing and swaying gently.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh God —</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin sees someone standing across the circle.</p><p class=\"action\">It’s him. Staring back. Wearing the same shirt.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quietly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">...what the hell?</p><p class=\"action\">The reflection blinks, but he doesn’t. Then disappears as if</p><p class=\"action\">it was never there.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You looked past the curtain, didn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you? What did it show you,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Nothing. Just... this place is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">getting to me.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(very calm)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They show us ourselves when it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">almost time.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone looks at him.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Time for what?</p><p class=\"action\">Harold smiles gently, like it’s already too late.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">For remembering who we are.</p><p class=\"action\">The humming builds again, vibrating their bones.</p><p class=\"action\">The candles gutter out one by one.</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 16</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. UNDERGROUND CHAMBER – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">The group enters a low-ceilinged room carved out of stone and</p><p class=\"action\">concrete.</p><p class=\"action\">Not ritualistic. Institutional. Old. Forgotten.</p><p class=\"action\">A metal cart sits against one wall.</p><p class=\"action\">A CRT television rests on top, thick glass screen dusty but</p><p class=\"action\">intact. Shelves line the walls. Hundreds of VHS tapes.</p><p class=\"action\">Handwritten labels. Dates. Names. The hum here is constant.</p><p class=\"action\">Electrical. Uneasy. Amber stops short.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This isn't a chamber. This is storage.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan steps closer to the shelves.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Storage for what?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin scans the labels. Names. Initials. Room numbers. Then he</p><p class=\"action\">freezes.</p><p class=\"action\">He pulls one tape from the shelf. Written in black marker:</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN PRICE. A date underneath. Recent</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">...That’s me.</p><p class=\"action\">No one jokes.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold steps back like the air just shifted.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(low)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That means it’s already been</p><p class=\"dialogue\">recorded.</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla tilts her head, smiling faintly.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They keep what we won’t look at.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin moves to the TV.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Ben, maybe don’t—</p><p class=\"action\">He slides the tape in.</p><p class=\"action\">The machine CLUNKS. Whirs.</p><p class=\"action\">Static. Then image.</p><p class=\"character\">ON SCREEN – BENJAMIN’S APARTMENT</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The footage is grainy. Fixed angle. Corner of the room.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin on-screen moves through the space, packing a box.</p><p class=\"action\">It’s real. Ordinary. Too quiet.</p><p class=\"action\">A phone vibrates on the table.</p><p class=\"action\">Voicemail plays through tinny speakers.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is my apartment...</p><p class=\"action\">A scene plays out. Benjamin packing a box, a voicemail from his</p><p class=\"action\">sister playing.</p><p class=\"character\">VOICEMAIL (V.O.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Ben, please just call me back. I'm</p><p class=\"dialogue\">worried about you.</p><p class=\"action\">He watches himself ignore the phone, isolate, spiral. Lets the</p><p class=\"action\">phone stop vibrating. In the room, real Benjamin can’t look away.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’ve been recording us.</p><p class=\"action\">On-screen Benjamin rewinds the tape.</p><p class=\"action\">Watches himself rewind it again.</p><p class=\"action\">The image glitches.</p><p class=\"action\">Now the on-screen Benjamin looks straight at the camera.</p><p class=\"action\">At them. The real Benjamin steps back.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t consent to this and I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">never did that. Turn it off.</p><p class=\"action\">The TV ejects the tape violently. It clatters to the floor.</p><p class=\"action\">Lights flicker. Another tape rattles on the shelf. Then</p><p class=\"action\">another. Harold covers his ears.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They don’t erase anything. They</p><p class=\"dialogue\">just keep it looping.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan grabs Benjamin’s arm.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This isn’t therapy. This is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">surveillance.</p><p class=\"action\">The TV flickers. A tape on the shelf beside the machine</p><p class=\"action\">SLIDES FORWARD slightly.</p><p class=\"action\">Just enough to be seen.</p><p class=\"action\">This one slides halfway out.</p><p class=\"action\">Written on it: REGAN</p><p class=\"action\">Regan stiffens.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh god. No.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Nope. Not doing that.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan reaches for the VCR. Amber stops her.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe you have to see it through. Some</p><p class=\"dialogue\">sort of immersion therapy?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t need to see it. I already</p><p class=\"dialogue\">lived it.</p><p class=\"action\">The TV turns back on. Static.</p><p class=\"character\">ON THE TV: HOSPITAL ROOM - NIGHT</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Regan lies unconscious in a bed.</p><p class=\"action\">Nurses argue quietly near the door.</p><p class=\"character\">NURSE #1 (V.O.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’re saying it was accidental.</p><p class=\"character\">NURSE #2 (V.O.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Doesn’t look accidental to me.</p><p class=\"action\">In the hallway beyond — Regan’s MOTHER sobs into her hands.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh god.</p><p class=\"action\">She backs away from the screen.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This isn't treatment. This is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">evidence.</p><p class=\"action\">The static does not stop.</p><p class=\"action\">The image bleeds past the edges of the screen.</p><p class=\"action\">The sound hums through the walls.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone else hears noise.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan hears words.</p><p class=\"action\">She presses her hands to her ears.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quiet, scared)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s not just sound. It’s... behind</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it. Like it knows I’m listening.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Its so loud.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What do you mean “behind it”?</p><p class=\"action\">The TV flicker harder. Static spikes. The image warps only</p><p class=\"action\">when Regan speaks. Benjamin notices. Regan puts her hands</p><p class=\"action\">over her ears.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Stop</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(to Amber)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you see that?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">See what?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin steps closer to the TV. Nothing changes. He guides</p><p class=\"action\">Regan by the shoulders to take one step back. The static</p><p class=\"action\">drops instantly. Everyone clocks it.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why did it stop?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Regan... did it stop because of you?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Nobody touched it.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan doesn’t answer. The TV clicks back on by itself. This</p><p class=\"action\">time- no video. Just sound. A low tone. Almost</p><p class=\"action\">conversational. Regan winces.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(low, realizing)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s not watching us.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s watching through you.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh HELL NO. I didn’t ask for this! I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">don't hear things.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Amber step toward Regan.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You didn’t before.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What? Why me?? I don't understand.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Turn this shit off!</p><p class=\"action\">She steps forward again. The TV shrieks. The speakers</p><p class=\"action\">distort. The image bends inward. Regan reaches for the TV.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Regan—don’t—</p><p class=\"action\">The moment she touches the TV, a searing flash. A burn tears</p><p class=\"action\">across her palm.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">AH! It burned me!</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re bleeding—oh my God—here—</p><p class=\"action\">Amber grabs a strip of cloth from her sleeve and wraps Regan’s</p><p class=\"action\">hand.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin doesn’t move. He's staring at the TV. The screen</p><p class=\"action\">stabilizes and the image shifts on its own Not Benjamin's</p><p class=\"action\">apartment, back to Regan's hospital room.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (LOW)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s not reacting to the machine.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s reacting to you.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t say that.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan winces.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s louder when I’m close.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin turns—</p><p class=\"action\">He sees something that stops him cold.</p><p class=\"action\">Another version of himself walking calmly past the archway. Same</p><p class=\"action\">clothes.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">... What the hell?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Ben?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I just watched myself leave.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re seeing it now. The closer we</p><p class=\"dialogue\">get, the more time folds.</p><p class=\"action\">Without warning, Lucy appears in the far corner. No one saw her</p><p class=\"action\">arrive.</p><p class=\"action\">She tilts her head, face calm but it glitches, her eyes stuttering</p><p class=\"action\">side to side, her body strobing in and out of place.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Lucy?</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The veil thins.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How long have you been standing there?</p><p class=\"action\">Lucy flickers and is gone. No one follows up.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to go. Now.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Time doesn’t work right down here.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Move.</p><p class=\"action\">They run.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. STAIRWELL – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin glances sideways.</p><p class=\"action\">Through a slit in the stairwell wall, he sees himself again —</p><p class=\"action\">standing in the dark. Watching. Motionless.</p><p class=\"action\">Their eyes lock. Then he vanishes.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. UPPER HALLWAY – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">They step into a freshly cleaned hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">The floors gleam.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls are perfectly still.</p><p class=\"action\">It’s quiet.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Back to normal?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever that is.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">All prisons feel clean before the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">execution.</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone stands in silence.</p><p class=\"action\">Just breathing.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 17</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ABANDONED WARD – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Regan lies awake on a stripped hospital cot, eyes open,</p><p class=\"action\">staring at the ceiling. She has not moved in hours.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber sleeps on the floor in the corner, wrapped in a thin</p><p class=\"action\">blanket. Her sleep is shallow. She shifts. Her hand twitches</p><p class=\"action\">like she is reacting to something unseen.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stands at the window. He watches the corridor beyond</p><p class=\"action\">the glass. Shadows stretch and curl across the floor and</p><p class=\"action\">walls. They move slowly, like fingers searching.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber opens her eyes. She watches Benjamin for a moment</p><p class=\"action\">before speaking.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(glancing at Regan)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She didn’t sleep at all.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber sits up, rubbing her face.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Neither did you.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan exhales, frustrated.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I can feel it now.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">All the time. Like something’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">right under my skin.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin turns from the window.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The room downstairs.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever that was. It reacted when</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you were close.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan sits up.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t do anything.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I know.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber reaches for a small cloth pouch beside her. The fabric is</p><p class=\"action\">worn thin. She opens it and spills the contents onto the floor.</p><p class=\"action\">Old tokens. Folded scraps of paper. Torn drawings. Repeated</p><p class=\"action\">shapes.</p><p class=\"action\">She picks up an old iron key.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This opens the ward past the south</p><p class=\"dialogue\">staircase. No one goes there.</p><p class=\"action\">She looks between them.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think we should.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin studies the key, uneasy but nodding.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan hesitates, then swings her legs off the cot.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. SOUTH WING – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The hallway is decayed.</p><p class=\"action\">Mold creeps up the walls. Paint peels in long strips. Doors</p><p class=\"action\">are scratched and barely hanging on rusted hinges.</p><p class=\"action\">Cracked fluorescent lights buzz overhead. Some flicker. Some</p><p class=\"action\">stay dark.</p><p class=\"action\">The sound follows them.</p><p class=\"action\">They stop at the final door.</p><p class=\"action\">It is intact.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber places her hand on it, then pulls back.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It's cold.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber inserts the key.</p><p class=\"action\">The lock resists, then clicks open.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. SEALED ROOM – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">They step inside.</p><p class=\"action\">The room is arranged deliberately.</p><p class=\"action\">Candles burned down to wax stumps line the perimeter.</p><p class=\"action\">Mirrors are mounted along the walls, every one of them</p><p class=\"action\">covered with black cloth.</p><p class=\"action\">In the center of the room sits a glass display case.</p><p class=\"action\">Inside it is a flat object.</p><p class=\"action\">Cracked. Worn. Marked with symbols that no one comments on.</p><p class=\"action\">A small marker rests near its center.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan stops short.</p><p class=\"action\">She stares at it longer than she means to.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is that.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin steps closer to the glass.</p><p class=\"action\">He squints.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber scans the room instead of the object.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This feels like more storage. Not a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">shrine.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan moves closer to the case.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then why seal it like this.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber reaches up and pulls the cloth from one of the mirrors.</p><p class=\"action\">The reflection reveals Regan standing there.</p><p class=\"action\">Her reflection’s mouth moves.</p><p class=\"action\">It speaks silently.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan freezes.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you see that.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin looks at the mirror.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No.</p><p class=\"action\">A sharp crack splits the air.</p><p class=\"action\">The glass display fractures slightly.</p><p class=\"action\">Inside, the marker shifts.</p><p class=\"action\">Not far. Just enough to be noticed.</p><p class=\"action\">The lights flicker.</p><p class=\"action\">The temperature drops fast.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan inhales sharply.</p><p class=\"action\">In the far corner of the room, Lucy stands.</p><p class=\"action\">She is already there.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not supposed to stare at it.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How long have you been there.</p><p class=\"action\">Lucy smiles faintly. Not kind. Not cruel. She turns and walks into</p><p class=\"action\">the dark. She disappears behind a shelf. Regan's voice tightens.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why does this keep reacting to me?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know why.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin looks back at the glass.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don't touch it.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan steps forward anyway. Glass crunches under her shoes. She</p><p class=\"action\">stops inches from the case.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I'm not touching it.</p><p class=\"action\">The candles blow out. A cold air rushes through the room. The</p><p class=\"action\">walls flicker. For a fraction of a second, the room drops out.</p><p class=\"action\">Darkness. Regan gasps and stumbles back. The lights return.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan’s eyes widen. Benjamin and Amber stare at her.</p><p class=\"action\">From the shadows:</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did you hear something?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No.</p><p class=\"action\">The hum settles back in. Low. Constant. Uninterested.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"action\">---------------------CONTINUE HERE---------------------</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 18</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. SEALED ROOM – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">The room is darker than before. Shadows bend unnaturally</p><p class=\"action\">across the walls. The candles are dead. Cold air hovers like</p><p class=\"action\">fog.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan stands frozen, her hand still on the marker. No one</p><p class=\"action\">speaks at first — they all just breathe, watching the smoke-</p><p class=\"action\">like tendrils swirl above the board encased in glass.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There are rules... Ways people say</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you can destroy a Ouija board. We</p><p class=\"dialogue\">can destroy it. But we have to be</p><p class=\"dialogue\">careful.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What kind of rules?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Break it into seven pieces. Burn</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it. Bury the ashes.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s a lot of superstition. Do</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you actually believe that?</p><p class=\"action\">Amber pauses. She gestures around the room where obviously</p><p class=\"action\">supernatural events take place.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(Sarcastic)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">....... yeah.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think this place pulled something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">out of it. And now... it can’t get</p><p class=\"dialogue\">back in.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin frowns — looking at the warped mirror cloths.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Out of where? The board?</p><p class=\"action\">Amber looks around the room slowly.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The mirrors... covered in black.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like a wake. Old tradition — you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">cover mirrors to stop spirits from</p><p class=\"dialogue\">finding their way back.</p><p class=\"action\">She walks to the nearest one, gripping the edge of the cloth.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Leave it wrapped up nice and tight.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It bites when it sees the light.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber yanks it anyway.</p><p class=\"action\">Behind the cloth: a mirror, blackened at the edges, the glass</p><p class=\"action\">warped like it caught fire from the inside.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Look at this. And...</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(leaning closer)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The board.</p><p class=\"action\">They crowd around the glass case again. Beneath the marker</p><p class=\"action\">lies a warped, aged board — cracked down its center, split</p><p class=\"action\">into jagged fragments. Ash dust clings to the display</p><p class=\"action\">interior.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s already been burned.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But it wasn’t buried.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So... what happens if we just leave</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it here? Let it rot and whisper to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">itself?</p><p class=\"action\">The board inside the case begins to tremble. A hum builds</p><p class=\"action\">from the walls — not mechanical, but alive, like breath</p><p class=\"action\">behind drywall.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly—</p><p class=\"action\">The marker slams against the glass and jerks to a letter:</p><p class=\"character\">“B.”</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then again: “U.” “R.” “Y.”</p><p class=\"character\">SPIRIT VOICE (V.O.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">BURY. END. BURY.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s trying to finish what someone</p><p class=\"dialogue\">else started.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We shouldn’t be hearing this.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat, almost a whisper)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(MORE)</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’re not supposed to be this close</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to knowing.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls begin to pulse, slow and wet — like lungs</p><p class=\"action\">expanding. The room fills with thick gray smoke. It doesn’t</p><p class=\"action\">choke, but it clings. Feels aware.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to move. Now.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber yanks the glass lid off. Regan reaches down — lifts the</p><p class=\"action\">board, her palm still bandaged and bloody. The board smokes</p><p class=\"action\">faintly, but she holds it firm.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where do we even take this? We</p><p class=\"dialogue\">can’t get outside. The windows</p><p class=\"dialogue\">don’t open. The exits—</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There’s one place.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">(pulls parchment from her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">pouch)</p><p class=\"action\">There’s a section on the layout we</p><p class=\"action\">haven’t been to. No label. Just a</p><p class=\"action\">symbol.</p><p class=\"action\">She shows the crude map. One corner marked with an X inside a</p><p class=\"action\">circle.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Seriously? Did you build this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place? Why do you know all of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">this?? Fuck it. Let's go.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I pay attention.</p><p class=\"action\">He opens the door. Cold air rushes in like something waiting.</p><p class=\"action\">Behind them, the board hisses softly. The marker twitches.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If it’s wrong... If it’s all part</p><p class=\"dialogue\">of a game...</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then we play it louder. Until the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">walls remember the notes.</p><p class=\"action\">The group exits, the board in Regan’s hands, the smoke</p><p class=\"action\">curling behind them, whispering like wind across a grave.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 16</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DIM HALLWAY – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The group hurries through the final unexplored corridor. The</p><p class=\"action\">shadows don’t move — they watch.</p><p class=\"action\">A door at the end bears no label. Just a faint impression in the</p><p class=\"action\">wood, like a hand print burned there long ago.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls drip with condensation. Every light they pass buzzes,</p><p class=\"action\">then dies behind them.</p><p class=\"action\">At the end: a door with no label. No knob. Just a worn black</p><p class=\"action\">cross.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin places his hand on it. It opens on its own.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ABANDONED CHAPEL – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">They step into a forgotten chapel space.</p><p class=\"action\">Pews overturned. Altar shattered. Moss creeps up cracked walls,</p><p class=\"action\">curling toward burned prayer candles long cold.</p><p class=\"action\">But the space is still. Dry. The air doesn’t hum here.</p><p class=\"action\">A strange peaceful unease fills the room.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe we shouldn’t be doing this.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You said this was the last place on</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the map.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yeah, but that doesn’t mean we’re</p><p class=\"dialogue\">supposed to mess with it. Ouija boards</p><p class=\"dialogue\">are... They’re doorways. Garbage</p><p class=\"dialogue\">disguised as toys. You don’t just open</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a door and hope for the best.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We didn’t open it.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No, but someone did. And every time we</p><p class=\"dialogue\">touch it, we feed it.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I wish we’d never started this. I wish</p><p class=\"dialogue\">we’d just left it in the dirt where it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">belongs.</p><p class=\"action\">She steps back, visibly shaken. Her hands tremble. Carmilla gently</p><p class=\"action\">touches her arm.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But we didn’t close the door, did we?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So now something’s coming through.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (SOFTLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ve read stories. People</p><p class=\"dialogue\">disappearing. People going mad. It</p><p class=\"dialogue\">doesn’t just let go.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then help us end it.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber takes a breath, steadies herself. She kneels where the altar</p><p class=\"action\">once stood, the stone cracked and blackened.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Right here. If anything’s sacred in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here... it’s this.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan steps forward and places the board on the ground.</p><p class=\"action\">It immediately pulses with heat — faint smoke rising from its</p><p class=\"action\">edges.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let’s bury it. Now.</p><p class=\"action\">They begin to break the chapel floor, stone by brittle stone.</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN pauses, squinting at something under the cracked slab. In</p><p class=\"action\">a flash hallucination — he sees a hand buried in the soil,</p><p class=\"action\">reaching up, its fingers twitching before dissolving into dust.</p><p class=\"action\">He says nothing. Keeps digging.</p><p class=\"action\">Beneath: soil. Real, untouched earth.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How is this here?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like it always was. Even before the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">building.</p><p class=\"action\">They dig deeper, until the hole is wide enough.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan picks up the board with both hands.</p><p class=\"action\">The marker spins violently, then flies off, slamming into the</p><p class=\"action\">nearest wall and cracking.</p><p class=\"action\">The board screeches softly — a sound like wind through teeth.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (WARNING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever happens next... don’t speak</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to it again.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh, I won't.</p><p class=\"action\">She lowers the board in.</p><p class=\"action\">It shakes. Then settles.</p><p class=\"action\">They begin covering it with soil.</p><p class=\"action\">As the dirt touches the surface, the lights in the chapel dim —</p><p class=\"action\">not flicker, but fade, like something dying quietly.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you feel that?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Less... noise.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s like... something stopped.</p><p class=\"action\">They pat the dirt down with their hands. Benjamin looks up — and</p><p class=\"action\">for the first time since waking here, the silence feels real.</p><p class=\"action\">Then: a soft creak from behind them.</p><p class=\"action\">They all turn.</p><p class=\"action\">Lucy stands in the chapel doorway.</p><p class=\"action\">Head tilted. Barefoot.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You buried it?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yes.</p><p class=\"action\">Lucy walks forward. Her footsteps make no sound.</p><p class=\"action\">She stands over the fresh soil.</p><p class=\"character\">LUCY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Sometimes... things grow back.</p><p class=\"action\">She smiles. Not unkindly. Then walks out without another word.</p><p class=\"action\">Nobody questions it.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What now?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We see if anything changes.</p><p class=\"action\">They remain still for a moment.</p><p class=\"action\">Nothing stirs. No voices. No glitches. Just... quiet.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 17</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ABANDONED CHAPEL – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Regan stands over the place where the board is buried, hands</p><p class=\"action\">trembling, her bandage soaked through.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin crouches beside the hole, packing down damp earth, his</p><p class=\"action\">fingers numb from cold.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber paces anxiously, her boots clicking across broken stone.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly—Candles relight. One by one.</p><p class=\"action\">A ring of flame builds around the chapel’s perimeter — flickering,</p><p class=\"action\">coordinated, sentient.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (WHISPERS)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It knows.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls tremble. Not violently — rhythmically, like a heartbeat.</p><p class=\"action\">The soil shifts — heaving, resisting.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hold it down!</p><p class=\"action\">He presses both hands into the dirt. It’s like pressing against</p><p class=\"action\">muscle — the board thrums beneath.</p><p class=\"action\">REGAN drops to her knees and shoves with him, their arms shaking</p><p class=\"action\">with effort.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s trying to climb back out!</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You have to say it!</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Say what?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Goodbye. That’s the final rule. You</p><p class=\"dialogue\">have to close the circle!</p><p class=\"action\">Regan takes a breath.</p><p class=\"action\">The air turns thick and soupy — her voice struggles to rise above</p><p class=\"action\">it.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You told me not to speak to it!!</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">SAY GOOD BYE!!</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (YELLING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">GOODBYE!!!</p><p class=\"action\">A beat.</p><p class=\"action\">Nothing.</p><p class=\"action\">Then —</p><p class=\"character\">CRACK!</p><p class=\"dialogue\">A thunderous snap from above — like the ceiling breaking in half.</p><p class=\"action\">All the candles blow out at once.</p><p class=\"action\">Darkness. The board stops moving. The soil flattens. The room</p><p class=\"action\">exhales. The hum... disappears.</p><p class=\"action\">Just silence.</p><p class=\"action\">They stare. Listen. The silence feels genuine — not imposed.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (SOFTLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did it work?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know. But if we stay here...</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It might not matter.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The corridor seems... normal.</p><p class=\"action\">Clean. Still. Smells faintly of disinfectant and lemon polish —</p><p class=\"action\">too clean, like a reset button was pressed.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It feels lighter.</p><p class=\"action\">They walk slowly, eyes wide. As they near the common room, they</p><p class=\"action\">see Otto, standing at the far end of the hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">Unmoving. Silent.</p><p class=\"action\">His eyes are glassy, unreadable.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where did you go?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We buried it. We finished it.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto doesn’t respond. He just stares past them.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (QUIETLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No one ever really finishes it.</p><p class=\"action\">He turns. Begins walking down a side corridor. Flickers once. Then</p><p class=\"action\">vanishes behind a wall that wasn’t there a moment ago.</p><p class=\"action\">The group stands frozen, unsure what just passed.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 18</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The room feels untouched, frozen in time. A radio plays faint</p><p class=\"action\">static in the background. Benjamin, Regan, and Amber enter</p><p class=\"action\">slowly.</p><p class=\"action\">Then — a bloodcurdling scream. Malachai sits on the floor,</p><p class=\"action\">arms wrapped around himself, staring blankly ahead.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t do it. He just climbed</p><p class=\"dialogue\">inside me.</p><p class=\"action\">The room lights flicker. An orderly appears and places a hand</p><p class=\"action\">on his shoulder.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Is it my turn?? Does my mom miss</p><p class=\"dialogue\">me?</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai doesn’t resist. He’s taken away —but looks directly</p><p class=\"action\">at Benjamin as he's led off.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto sits at the window, back turned.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He’s been off since we got back.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He was always strange. But now</p><p class=\"dialogue\">he’s... Quiet.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Quiet Otto is terrifying.</p><p class=\"action\">They watch as Otto hums to himself, fingers twitching</p><p class=\"action\">rhythmically on the arm of his chair. He mutters under his</p><p class=\"action\">breath —barely audible.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Circles... ash... open-and-shut... burn</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the name... never the bone...</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That doesn’t sound like him.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. It doesn’t.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber edges forward, cautiously.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto? Are you feeling okay?</p><p class=\"action\">He stops humming. Slowly turns. His eyes are darker—almost</p><p class=\"action\">sunken. His mouth twists into a grin that doesn’t reach his</p><p class=\"action\">eyes.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You thought it would end. When you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">buried it. Silly girl.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What did you say?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (SUDDENLY LOUDER)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You buried wood. Not intention.</p><p class=\"action\">The lights flicker. The radio hisses, then reverses itself,</p><p class=\"action\">spitting out garbled words backward.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Something followed us out. Or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">someone invited it.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto rises slowly, his bones cracking, but his body doesn’t</p><p class=\"action\">react to the pain. It's too fluid. Almost borrowed.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There must always be a host.</p><p class=\"action\">He turns and walks out of the room without another word.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh no. Oh no no no...</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He’s possessed. Isn’t he?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or worse—maybe he always was.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The group stands in stunned silence. Amber checks the</p><p class=\"action\">hallway, but Otto is gone.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly, from behind the couch—JACE emerges, arms crossed.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You buried something you didn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">understand, didn’t you?</p><p class=\"action\">They all jump.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where the hell have you been?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (DRYLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Avoiding this circus.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We thought you were gone.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I tried. Hallway looped three</p><p class=\"dialogue\">times, then I ended up in the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">kitchen.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Only the coffee was missing.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Explain that. How the fuck do I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">survive this place without coffee?</p><p class=\"action\">He steps forward, eyes scanning them. He stops on Regan.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You're bleeding again.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan looks down — her bandage is fresh, but a line of blood</p><p class=\"action\">trails down her wrist.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t feel anything.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s the problem. You’re numb.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to stick together. Otto’s—</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (INTERRUPTING) —</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Unstable! No kidding. He’s been</p><p class=\"dialogue\">whispering to the air since I got</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you think it’s the board? Still</p><p class=\"dialogue\">active?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think you buried a matchstick in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a bonfire.</p><p class=\"action\">He walks to the window Otto had been sitting at and looks</p><p class=\"action\">out.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There’s something in the courtyard.</p><p class=\"action\">They all gather behind him.</p><p class=\"action\">Outside: no one. Just flickering shadows.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—Otto’s silhouette passes by. He’s walking into the east</p><p class=\"action\">wing. Alone.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We have to follow him.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hell no. I ain't doing a damn</p><p class=\"dialogue\">thing. All I am doing is my time</p><p class=\"dialogue\">until I can leave this place.</p><p class=\"action\">They exchange glances. No one speaks.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 19</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. SOUTHEAST WING – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">An alarm pulses faintly in the background, like a heartbeat</p><p class=\"action\">on life support. The hallway is choked in red emergency</p><p class=\"action\">light, casting long, fractured shadows along the decaying</p><p class=\"action\">walls.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan, Benjamin, and Amber move fast, flinching at every</p><p class=\"action\">echoing groan.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe he is a vessel.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">A what?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The thing in the board—maybe it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">using him to anchor itself here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So if we stop Otto— I mean, help</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto....</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We might stop it.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. TREATMENT ROOM – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The door creaks open — metal scraping against metal. Inside,</p><p class=\"action\">a rotted therapy room, and at its center: Otto, crouched on</p><p class=\"action\">all fours, drawing a massive sigil with trembling, blood-</p><p class=\"action\">soaked hands. The symbol pulses, wet and breathing.</p><p class=\"action\">His head jerks unnaturally as they enter — as if strings were</p><p class=\"action\">yanked.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You shouldn’t be here.</p><p class=\"action\">His voice is hollow. Somewhere between a whisper and a growl.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto—fight it. Whatever’s inside</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you—</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (SHAKING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There’s no Otto. Just... the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">vessel.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is wrong. This is so wrong.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto’s back arches sharply, bones cracking. His eyes roll</p><p class=\"action\">back. A black mist begins curling out of his mouth, coiling</p><p class=\"action\">above him like smoke forming a shape.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh God.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto screams — but the scream is layered — both human and</p><p class=\"action\">something inhuman beneath.</p><p class=\"action\">The lights explode, glass raining down.</p><p class=\"action\">The sigil glows red-hot — the floor around it burns in a</p><p class=\"action\">perfect ring.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto’s body levitates, limbs trembling, head lolled back.</p><p class=\"action\">From his chest, the black mist grows into a snaking tendril—</p><p class=\"action\">reaching for the ceiling, searching.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (SCREAMING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">NO!</p><p class=\"action\">She rushes forward and grabs a nearby metal lamp, smashing it</p><p class=\"action\">directly into the center of the sigil.</p><p class=\"action\">The mist SHRIEKS. The circle spasms with electricity.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto speaks again — voice now fractured, glitching.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (SHIFTED, OVERLAPPED)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some must stay. Some must hold.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some must—</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Nobody’s staying. You don’t get to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">decide that!</p><p class=\"action\">Amber reaches into her pouch and pulls out the last relic — a</p><p class=\"action\">shard of burned summoning glass from the chamber.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin—help me. Now!</p><p class=\"action\">They drop to their knees and begin etching a new circle</p><p class=\"action\">around Otto using the shard, dragging it through the tile.</p><p class=\"action\">The sound is like nails across bone.</p><p class=\"action\">Otto begins convulsing midair, blood trailing from his nose</p><p class=\"action\">and ears. The black mist thrashes violently.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (TEARS IN HER VOICE)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto—if you’re still in there—</p><p class=\"dialogue\">please...</p><p class=\"action\">The mist turns toward Regan, the shape nearly humanoid now —</p><p class=\"action\">thin, tall, crawling with faces.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber slams the shard into the ground to complete the circle.</p><p class=\"character\">A BLINDING FLASH—</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The mist shrieks, recoils, and slams into the floor,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">disappearing in a blast of wind and smoke that blows out the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">remaining bulbs and knocks them all backward.</p><p class=\"character\">SILENCE.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">For a moment, nothing moves.</p><p class=\"action\">Then Otto collapses, slamming to the floor with a dull thud.</p><p class=\"action\">He gasps—coughing, blinking like someone pulled from</p><p class=\"action\">drowning.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (HOARSE, HUMAN)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What... happened?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re okay. You’re okay.</p><p class=\"action\">He starts to cry—silent, uncontrollable sobs.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber wraps her arms around him. Benjamin sits back, shaking,</p><p class=\"action\">his hands covered in ash and blood.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 20</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. TREATMENT ROOM – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The sigil is now a charcoal scar baked into the tile. A single</p><p class=\"action\">overhead fixture flickers, struggling to stay lit. Otto lies on a</p><p class=\"action\">wheeled cot, wrapped in a blanket, murmuring half-dream words.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Is it over?</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">For now... but we don’t know what’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">still inside him.</p><p class=\"action\">The door creaks open.</p><p class=\"action\">ANNA steps in. She’s perfectly composed, but something is... off:</p><p class=\"action\">Her voice is a shade higher, almost sing-song-y.</p><p class=\"action\">A jelly bracelet peeks from under her starched cuff.</p><p class=\"action\">Her earrings are tiny plastic stars that don’t match her usual</p><p class=\"action\">minimalist style.</p><p class=\"action\">She shuts the door and faces them with a smile that’s a fraction</p><p class=\"action\">too wide.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello! There you are. I’ve been</p><p class=\"dialogue\">looking everywhere, guys.</p><p class=\"action\">The casual “guys” lands strangely in the quiet room.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Doctor, Otto was—</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(glances at Otto)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">—floating. Something took him over.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto’s always been a bit theatrical.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Creative minds need... boundaries.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We all saw it. That wasn’t theater.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna strolls to the ruined symbol, crouches. She traces an edge</p><p class=\"action\">with one gloved fingertip, like a teenager testing wet paint.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hmm... spooky.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(turns to them)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’ve made such a mess. I’ll have to,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">y’know, fix this.</p><p class=\"action\">She gives a half-shrug that looks more high-school hallway than</p><p class=\"action\">clinical authority.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You know that isn’t some art project.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna’s smile flickers—just a second—then resets.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe some things don’t need</p><p class=\"dialogue\">explaining. Stories can get... out of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hand.</p><p class=\"action\">She rises, dusting imaginary dirt off her coat. Under the</p><p class=\"action\">fluorescents the jelly bracelet seems to glow.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Doctor—are you all right?</p><p class=\"action\">Anna pauses, humming a tune under her breath—an old 1990s lullaby</p><p class=\"action\">that definitely does not fit the sterile room. She catches</p><p class=\"action\">herself, clears her throat.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Everyone needs rest. Especially Otto.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(cheerfully)</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(MORE)</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please find some peace and quiet,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">’kay?</p><p class=\"action\">The little “’kay?” slips out before she can smooth it over. Her</p><p class=\"action\">cheeks color—tiny, startled embarrassment—then she’s professional</p><p class=\"action\">again.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That didn’t feel like a story.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna’s eyes flick to Benjamin—an odd mix of adult patience and</p><p class=\"action\">teenage challenge —then she heads to the door. Just before</p><p class=\"action\">exiting, she murmurs almost to herself:</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Mom’s gonna—</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(catch)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I mean—this is not good.</p><p class=\"action\">She exits, humming the lullaby. Door clicks shut.</p><p class=\"character\">AFTERMATH</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The four stare at the door.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did she just say Mom? I don't like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that she didn't say goodbye.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(scowls)</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And... “’kay.” She never talks like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that.</p><p class=\"action\">From the cot, Otto mumbles a lucid fragment:</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Girl at the board... hands like glass...</p><p class=\"action\">He drifts back into uneasy sleep.</p><p class=\"action\">JACE appears in the doorway, arms folded.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Our friendly shrink just called us</p><p class=\"dialogue\">guys. I’d call that a red flag.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or a glitch. Like everything else.</p><p class=\"action\">They all look down at the smoking sigil, then at Otto.</p><p class=\"action\">The fixture above them finally dies, plunging the room into</p><p class=\"action\">darkness lit only by hallway glow. No one moves.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 21</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. GROUP THERAPY ROOM – NEXT MORNING</p><p class=\"action\">Morning light barely pierces the grime-streaked windows,</p><p class=\"action\">casting long, fractured shadows across a circle of mismatched</p><p class=\"action\">chairs.</p><p class=\"action\">The air is stale, like it hasn’t moved in weeks.</p><p class=\"action\">ANNA stands at the front, clutching a clipboard too tightly.</p><p class=\"action\">Her smile is pasted on—cheerful but brittle.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello, everyone. I’m so glad you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">all made it today. I just love when</p><p class=\"dialogue\">we’re all together.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let’s take a moment to share how</p><p class=\"dialogue\">we’re feeling, one at a time. Okay?</p><p class=\"action\">Her voice lands wrong. Too light. Too practiced. Like she's</p><p class=\"action\">performing.</p><p class=\"action\">Amber shifts in her seat. Regan glares. Benjamin doesn’t</p><p class=\"action\">move.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto? You had a hard day yesterday.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Want to start us off?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(voice distant)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">There was... something. Not just a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">voice. Something else. Something in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">me.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna smiles too wide. Her pen trembles over the clipboard.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s... wonderful insight.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(chirpy)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But how could that even be?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Because it was. And you know it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">was. Don’t patronize us.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It wasn’t psychosis. We saw it. We</p><p class=\"dialogue\">all saw it.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And if you say it’s just our minds</p><p class=\"dialogue\">again, I swear—</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Let’s not get hostile. The energy</p><p class=\"dialogue\">in the room is... shifting.</p><p class=\"character\">POP.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">A fluorescent bulb explodes overhead, raining sparks. No one</p><p class=\"dialogue\">flinches.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s the third one this week.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Look.</p><p class=\"action\">She points to the back wall. The paint ripples—breathing.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s breaking down. The illusion.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The drugs. Something’s failing.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna edges backward, her posture less doctor, more relaxed.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe its time for... for some</p><p class=\"dialogue\">quiet reflection.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (STANDING SHARPLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She doesn’t see it. She can’t see</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (SNAPPING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">YES SHE CAN!</p><p class=\"action\">Everyone jumps. Regan’s face is red, fists clenched.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not some clueless counselor!</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You know what’s happening—you’ve</p><p class=\"dialogue\">always known. Why else would you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">keep us here?</p><p class=\"action\">Anna freezes mid-step, eyes wide, mouth slightly open.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (SOFTLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I... I didn’t mean...please calm</p><p class=\"dialogue\">down. It spins in here when you get</p><p class=\"dialogue\">angry.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(mean, desperate)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What are you? A prison guard? A</p><p class=\"dialogue\">puppet?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or just some scared little girl in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a lab coat playing make-believe?</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quiet, almost childish)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s not fair...</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. What’s not fair is lying to us</p><p class=\"dialogue\">while people vanish. While we drown</p><p class=\"dialogue\">in this place.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Something’s coming again.</p><p class=\"action\">From below—a metallic moan, like the bowels of the building</p><p class=\"action\">groaning. Then: bells. Deep, melodic... but distant.</p><p class=\"action\">No bells exist in this hospital.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA (WHISPERS AND DANCES)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Do you hear that?</p><p class=\"action\">HAROLD steps into the room from the hall, wild-eyed.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s starting again. Just like the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">night Lucy glitched.</p><p class=\"action\">The group instinctively forms a tight inner circle.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna hugs the clipboard to her chest like a schoolbook,</p><p class=\"action\">fingers trembling.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Everyone just... calm down.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s not gonna help. She’s as</p><p class=\"dialogue\">stuck as we are.</p><p class=\"action\">He leans in the doorway, silent until now.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But I’d like to know who’s pulling</p><p class=\"dialogue\">her strings.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna’s mouth opens—no sound comes out.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You want us quiet because we’re</p><p class=\"dialogue\">getting close.</p><p class=\"action\">Walls begin to swell again, expanding and contracting—</p><p class=\"action\">inhaling.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (MURMURING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The board never left. It just</p><p class=\"dialogue\">turned this place inside out.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (TO ANNA)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If you want to help us—prove it. Or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">stay out of our way.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna stares at her. Her eyes flicker—not blinking, flicker,</p><p class=\"action\">like static.</p><p class=\"action\">Then she turns and walks out without another word.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where is she going? She didn't say</p><p class=\"dialogue\">goodbye. Again! Why is she being so</p><p class=\"dialogue\">rude now? I thought words mattered!</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (GRAVELY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Probably where all the other ones</p><p class=\"dialogue\">go... before they disappear.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 22</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ACTIVITY ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The patients sit quietly around a long, sterile table. The lights</p><p class=\"action\">above flicker at regular intervals. Otto keeps to himself, eyes</p><p class=\"action\">never lifting. Regan eats slowly. Amber picks at her tray.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stares across the room.</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai hides under a table. Eyes glowing faintly.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I thought you left.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I never leave.</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai scratches at the floor and eventually curls into a</p><p class=\"action\">fetal position and cries.</p><p class=\"action\">The room is dim except for a small desk lamp on a table. Near the</p><p class=\"action\">end of the table sits HAROLD. He hums softly to himself. He is</p><p class=\"action\">usually folding napkins into tiny shapes— birds, flowers, and</p><p class=\"action\">stars. Tonight Harold sits alone, working on a puzzle.</p><p class=\"action\">Tonight, he hums louder.</p><p class=\"action\">A kitten puzzle. Only a few pieces left. He hums a tune, low and</p><p class=\"action\">off-key — something sweet and old-fashioned.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re still at that thing?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (SMILING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m almost done. Gotta finish it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">before we all go batty. There we</p><p class=\"dialogue\">go. Beautiful.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold, we need you in the rec room.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Jace found something behind the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">vending machines.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Always something, huh?</p><p class=\"action\">He places the final piece, then pauses. His hands rest on the</p><p class=\"action\">table. He leans back and closes his eyes. A long, peaceful breath</p><p class=\"action\">and begins folding a napkin into a bird.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—his eyes snap open. Something’s shifted. The clock on the</p><p class=\"action\">wall rewinds. The lamp flickers. He hears soft footsteps — even</p><p class=\"action\">though no one is behind him.</p><p class=\"action\">Harold stands. Slowly. Looks around. From the hallway, a soft</p><p class=\"action\">humming — familiar. The same tune he was humming.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No... no, please.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Can I just... sit for a few more</p><p class=\"dialogue\">minutes?</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ACTIVITY ROOM – SAME TIME</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold’s louder than usual.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t think he’s humming. I think</p><p class=\"dialogue\">he’s chanting.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin looks closer. Harold’s hands tremble.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold?</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I made it. I made it to the door. It's</p><p class=\"dialogue\">opening now. I’m going home.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What? They are letting you go? How??</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly, Harold drops the napkin had was holding. It flutters to</p><p class=\"action\">the floor. He looks up at them— serene.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD</p><p class=\"dialogue\">My wife.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Harold, what are you talking about?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are you OK??</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Harold stumbles into the hallway. Empty. The lights buzz overhead.</p><p class=\"action\">From the far end, two orderlies appear. No faces, no voices. Just</p><p class=\"action\">shadows in uniform.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CHOKING BACK TEARS)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Wait... wait! I remember now.</p><p class=\"action\">He presses himself against the wall as they move closer. Something</p><p class=\"action\">in him... shifts.</p><p class=\"action\">He clutches his chest.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I wasn’t always old. I had a wife. Her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">name was June. She wore lemon perfume.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(sobbing now)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She used to hum that song while</p><p class=\"dialogue\">painting in the kitchen. I’d</p><p class=\"dialogue\">forgotten. I’d forgotten her.</p><p class=\"action\">The orderlies stop just feet away.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t want to forget again.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please... I don’t want to forget her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">face.</p><p class=\"action\">The hallway light above him goes out. Everything is silent except</p><p class=\"action\">the hum.</p><p class=\"character\">HAROLD (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Tell them I loved them. Tell them I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">remembered.</p><p class=\"action\">He takes a step forward, shoulders straight, tears falling freely.</p><p class=\"action\">The orderlies guide Harold down the hall.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ACTIVITY ROOM – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The table is empty. The puzzle complete.</p><p class=\"action\">In Harold’s chair: a lemon-colored thread.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">They run into the hall. No one.</p><p class=\"action\">Just the sound of the wind, and the clock ticking forward again.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (BARELY AUDIBLE)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No...</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where is he? Did they release him?? We</p><p class=\"dialogue\">didn’t even get to say goodbye.</p><p class=\"action\">They stand in silence. The moment stretches.</p><p class=\"action\">Then, faintly — as if from behind the walls — they hear humming.</p><p class=\"action\">The same tune Harold sang. They listen. And they cry. Malachai</p><p class=\"action\">screams from the other room.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 23</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. WEST WING – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Thunder rolls low in the distance as the group gathers in the west</p><p class=\"action\">wing—a part of the hospital no one ever uses.</p><p class=\"action\">The hallway seems longer than usual, the lights too dim, as</p><p class=\"action\">if something unseen leaches energy from the walls. The</p><p class=\"action\">wallpaper bubbles like it's exhaling.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where’s Amber?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She said she was going to check on</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you, Otto. But that was an hour ago.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She wouldn’t leave. She couldn’t get</p><p class=\"dialogue\">far. Not without telling someone.</p><p class=\"action\">They walk slowly, past peeling wallpaper and rusted equipment. A</p><p class=\"action\">broken intercom hisses static, then cuts out.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—a soft, rhythmic clicking. They follow it down the corridor</p><p class=\"action\">until they reach a heavy metal door marked “ARCHIVES.” It groans</p><p class=\"action\">open.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. ARCHIVES ROOM – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Colder. Stiller. Dust clings in thick layers, stirred by their</p><p class=\"action\">breath.</p><p class=\"action\">File cabinets stretch deep into the shadows like tombstones.</p><p class=\"action\">In the center of the room—Amber’s journal, alone on the floor.</p><p class=\"action\">Open to a blank page.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Amber?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where is she?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She was afraid of this place. Said it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">watched her. Maybe... maybe it took</p><p class=\"dialogue\">her.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don't say that! And what do you mean</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I mean whatever is behind this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">whole... illusion. The hospital, the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">rooms—it’s changing. It’s not holding</p><p class=\"dialogue\">together anymore.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. She’s still here. She has to be.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(checking the corners)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What if she’s just somewhere we can’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">see?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or somewhere we’re not supposed to.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin kneels and picks up the journal.</p><p class=\"action\">The pages begin to flip on their own, as if something searches</p><p class=\"action\">through them. Faster. Faster—then it stops dead on a single page.</p><p class=\"action\">A symbol is scrawled in thick, black ink. Jagged, haphazard. Not</p><p class=\"action\">written—carved.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is it?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Same one from the circle Otto drew.</p><p class=\"action\">The floor rumbles. A low, subsonic tremor. Lights flicker</p><p class=\"action\">violently.</p><p class=\"action\">From deep in the shadows—a whisper.</p><p class=\"character\">AMBER (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t trust the walls...</p><p class=\"action\">They turn. Nothing. Just a filing cabinet drawer, slowly sliding</p><p class=\"action\">open on its own.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s... trapped in the layers of this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We're all trapped in this place.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. Not like that.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Before she disappeared, she was asking</p><p class=\"dialogue\">questions about Anna. Said something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">felt wrong about her.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You mean besides her talking like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">she’s reading from a script?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or how she always smells like burning</p><p class=\"dialogue\">incense. Think she’s afraid she’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">gonna catch the crazy?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Her office floats. It’s here, but it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">isn’t. Like a dream pretending to be a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">room.</p><p class=\"action\">They all stare blankly at Carmilla.</p><p class=\"action\">Beat.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The candles. Crystals. Mood lighting.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like a Pinterest board for witchcraft</p><p class=\"dialogue\">exploded. You think she is a witch?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Always lamps. Never ceiling lights.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe she is as afraid of this place</p><p class=\"dialogue\">as we are. Maybe it's protection</p><p class=\"dialogue\">spells.</p><p class=\"action\">They pause. The tremor stops. Everything is too quiet now.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Amber said Anna was pretending. Like a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">kid playing dress-up.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">SHE DOES sound rehearsed.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like she’s trying to remember lines.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not... feel them. Like being told what</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to say.</p><p class=\"action\">They mostly ignore Carmilla now, even though if they listen,</p><p class=\"action\">she makes the most sense.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It's almost ritualistic.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY OUTSIDE DR. ANNA'S OFFICE – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">They approach the heavy wooden door. Ornate. Out of place in the</p><p class=\"action\">hospital’s sterile architecture.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin leans in, ear against it.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s in there. I smell incense.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And I hear... music?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s too new. Too loud. Like laughing</p><p class=\"dialogue\">at a funeral.</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla mutter this under her breath with a smile that</p><p class=\"action\">doesn’t reach her eyes.</p><p class=\"action\">Inside, faint pop music plays. Then laughter—Anna’s voice, light,</p><p class=\"action\">joking with someone.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s not alone. Who is she talking</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin jiggles the handle. Locked. Otto slams his shoulder into</p><p class=\"action\">it. Nothing.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan notices the flicker of warm light under the door.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Everything else is falling apart... and</p><p class=\"dialogue\">this door is solid?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe it’s protected.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(almost sarcastically)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or dead-bolted.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(matter of fact)</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She is hiding something.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or holding something in.</p><p class=\"action\">They pound on the door.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Anna! Open up!</p><p class=\"action\">The music cuts. The laughter stops. Just silence now. And that</p><p class=\"action\">sickly-sweet smell of candles.</p><p class=\"action\">A whisper seeps through the door.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I didn’t mean to break it...</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (QUIET, TO HERSELF)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Break what?</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did she just confess?</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly, the light under the door disappears. The scent fades.</p><p class=\"action\">Nothing but heartbeat silence.</p><p class=\"action\">The group stands still.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think we just asked the right</p><p class=\"dialogue\">question. She's slipping.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 24</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. EMPTY COMMON ROOM – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The group sits in the dim light of the common room. A small lamp</p><p class=\"action\">flickers softly. Outside, wind rattles the windows.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stares into space. Regan paces near the window. Otto taps</p><p class=\"action\">his fingers, rhythmic and uneven. Carmilla clutches Amber’s</p><p class=\"action\">journal to her chest.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe... maybe we’re overreacting.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(over her shoulder)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Overreacting?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Look, Anna’s a doctor. She’s allowed a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">private life. Maybe she talks</p><p class=\"dialogue\">differently when she’s not treating</p><p class=\"dialogue\">us. Everyone wears a mask at work.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So incense and candlelight and</p><p class=\"dialogue\">whispering Latin is her me time?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She wasn’t alone in there. She was</p><p class=\"dialogue\">laughing like she hadn't a care in the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">world. It didn’t sound like her... or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">maybe it did. The real her.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe she is strange, but that doesn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">make her evil. We’re residents of this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">place, right?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t do that, Benjamin. Don’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">rationalize what you know feels wrong.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She wasn’t chatting. She was behaving</p><p class=\"dialogue\">like someone else.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Amber knew it. That’s why she started</p><p class=\"dialogue\">watching her.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And now Amber’s gone. What does that</p><p class=\"dialogue\">tell you?</p><p class=\"action\">Silence. Regan stops pacing. Carmilla sets the journal on the</p><p class=\"action\">table.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She didn’t scream. Didn’t vanish in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">front of us. Just... faded. Like her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">thread was clipped.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She was looking for truth. Maybe she</p><p class=\"dialogue\">found it.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(gritting his teeth)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I should have stopped her.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She was unraveling and I... I let her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">go alone.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She left her writings.</p><p class=\"action\">She opens the journal. A loose note tucked inside flutters free.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin catches it.</p><p class=\"action\">CLOSE-UP – the note reads:</p><p class=\"action\">\"She watches everything. But she can't see herself. Look at the</p><p class=\"action\">mirror. The real one.\"</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The mirror...</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The one in Anna’s office?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We never looked. We’ve been staring at</p><p class=\"dialogue\">her... not what’s behind her.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That mirror doesn’t reflect us. It</p><p class=\"dialogue\">reflects her. Who she really is.</p><p class=\"action\">A long beat. The wind outside builds. A door upstairs creaks, slow</p><p class=\"action\">and deliberate.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And if we look in it?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then maybe we finally see where we</p><p class=\"dialogue\">really are.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Amber was right. Anna’s not just</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hiding something.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She might be the only one holding the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">door shut. Or the only one who can</p><p class=\"dialogue\">open it.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Either way... we’re not getting out</p><p class=\"dialogue\">unless we face her.</p><p class=\"action\">Another long silence. Somewhere deep in the hospital, a child’s</p><p class=\"action\">giggle echoes faintly, then vanishes.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We stop pretending this is a hospital.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This is a trap. And we either die</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here... Or we break free.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 25</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. STAIRWELL – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The group stands at the bottom of the main stairwell. Above them,</p><p class=\"action\">the slow, heavy creaking continues—wood groaning, something</p><p class=\"action\">pacing.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan clutches the railing tightly.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s right above us.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Could be the old infirmary. No one’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">used that wing in decades.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">THEN WHY IS SOMEONE WALKING AROUND</p><p class=\"character\">UP THERE?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">A moment of silence. They all hear it: the deliberate pace of feet</p><p class=\"dialogue\">dragging just above them.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—it stops.</p><p class=\"action\">They exchange a look, then begin climbing. Each step is tense.</p><p class=\"action\">The creaking ceases as they reach the landing.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. UPPER FLOOR HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Dust coats the floor like snow. The air smells stale, metallic.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls feel narrower than usual—as though the hallway is gently</p><p class=\"action\">closing in.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s... small here.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Feels like a pressure change. Like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">altitude.</p><p class=\"action\">They glance at each other. For a flash—Carmilla sees Benjamin</p><p class=\"action\">blink, and for half a second, he’s covered in burn scars. She</p><p class=\"action\">flinches.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin—your face—</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What?</p><p class=\"action\">She stares. The scars are gone.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I saw the fire lick your skin.</p><p class=\"action\">She caresses his face with concern.</p><p class=\"action\">The hallway is lined with sealed rooms. All locked. Except one.</p><p class=\"action\">A single door—slightly ajar. A warm, pulsing glow seeps through</p><p class=\"action\">the gap.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. INFIRMARY – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Inside: abandoned beds, rusted IV stands, broken monitors. Glass</p><p class=\"action\">shards glitter in the moonlight.</p><p class=\"action\">At the far end of the room—a figure stands motionless. Too still.</p><p class=\"action\">Too dark.</p><p class=\"action\">Its eyes pitch black, its skin stretched thin. And then it tilts</p><p class=\"action\">its head.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (SHARP WHISPER)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Is that... Anna?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No.</p><p class=\"action\">It steps forward. The voice that escapes its mouth is Anna’s—</p><p class=\"action\">distorted and echoing.</p><p class=\"character\">ANNA-LIKE ENTITY</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You shouldn’t be here.</p><p class=\"action\">The voice overlaps with itself, like two recordings playing</p><p class=\"action\">slightly out of sync. The air warps, and Benjamin’s hand begins to</p><p class=\"action\">tremble.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s using her voice.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It's not just that. It’s not even</p><p class=\"dialogue\">solid. Look.</p><p class=\"action\">The figure flickers, momentarily revealing multiple versions of</p><p class=\"action\">itself—Anna... a young girl... a writhing shadow... and then back.</p><p class=\"action\">The walls breathe, a low inhale–exhale rhythm, slow and pulsing.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan grips a bedpost to steady herself.</p><p class=\"action\">Then— The entity lunges forward.</p><p class=\"action\">It stops abruptly, as though caught by an invisible wire. It lets</p><p class=\"action\">out a non-human screech, not in pain—but rage.</p><p class=\"action\">The floor trembles. The temperature drops.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">BACK OUT! NOW!</p><p class=\"action\">They stumble out, slamming the door behind them.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">They stand in the silence.</p><p class=\"action\">Except... they’re not standing together anymore.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan is suddenly alone—no one around her. She turns in panic. The</p><p class=\"action\">hallway stretches endlessly in both directions.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello?? Benjamin?! Otto?!</p><p class=\"action\">From the shadows—a voice answers in her own voice.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN 2 (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’re gone. And so are you.</p><p class=\"action\">She turns—and sees herself. Pale, blank-eyed, standing still just</p><p class=\"action\">a few feet away.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—blink—and it’s Benjamin in front of her again.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Regan?! What happened?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know. I saw... me.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We have to get out of this hallway.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The mirror...</p><p class=\"action\">They all turn.</p><p class=\"action\">Carmilla stares into a dusty mirror on the infirmary door—only</p><p class=\"action\">it’s not reflecting the hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">It shows all of them standing in different places, facing away</p><p class=\"action\">from each other.</p><p class=\"action\">And then: Amber appears in the reflection. Standing behind them.</p><p class=\"action\">But when they turn—she’s not there.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (WHISPERS)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s still here... somewhere.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly— the mirror shatters. Loud, unnatural. No object touched</p><p class=\"action\">it.</p><p class=\"action\">The creaking resumes—but now it’s directly beneath them.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need to move.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 26</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY OUTSIDE ANNA'S OFFICE – DAY</p><p class=\"action\">A sickly yellow light filters through the high windows.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin, Regan, and Otto stand again outside Anna's office.</p><p class=\"action\">This time, there is no laughter. Just silence.</p><p class=\"action\">The yellow glow filters through the windows, casting long,</p><p class=\"action\">warped shadows across the floor.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’ve been chasing symbols. Voices.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Vanishing people. What if we are</p><p class=\"dialogue\">circling the wrong truth?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What truth is there in a place like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">this?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">None of this is psychological. Not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">in the way she keeps telling us.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Made to look like a hospital to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">keep us docile. To keep us</p><p class=\"dialogue\">guessing.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This place isn’t a hospital. It’s a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">holding ground, a feeding ground.</p><p class=\"action\">They glance back at Anna’s door.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then who is she really?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whoever—or whatever—she is, she’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">keeping us in line.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then maybe it’s time we stop being</p><p class=\"dialogue\">polite about it.</p><p class=\"action\">They notice a faint glow beneath the door. This time, it</p><p class=\"action\">pulses with red instead of warm candlelight. As if it is</p><p class=\"action\">reacting.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That thing in the infirmary. I saw</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something there in its eyes. It</p><p class=\"dialogue\">knew us.</p><p class=\"action\">They turn and walk away from Anna’s office—more determined</p><p class=\"action\">than ever. The red under the door intensifies.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DINING HALL – LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The light outside is oddly gray, giving the room a washed-out</p><p class=\"action\">hue.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin, Regan, and Otto sit at their usual table. Trays of</p><p class=\"action\">untouched food sit before them, mold blooming along the edges</p><p class=\"action\">like time has warped again. Everything feels off-kilter.</p><p class=\"action\">Patients dot the room like statues.</p><p class=\"action\">A few other patients scatter the large hall, but they’re far</p><p class=\"action\">apart and eerily silent.</p><p class=\"action\">One rocks slowly, humming a nursery rhyme. – Another whispers</p><p class=\"action\">to the wall, weeping and giggling between breaths. – A third</p><p class=\"action\">stares blankly at a wall where there’s no window, mouthing</p><p class=\"action\">silent words.</p><p class=\"action\">A man closer to the window cries softly, hands over his face.</p><p class=\"action\">Their presence feels ghost like—there, yet unreachable.</p><p class=\"action\">At the far end, someone laughs into their empty hands.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Has anyone else noticed we haven’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">seen an orderly in... Days?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Gone. No shifts. Not even for meds.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Not that they ever did much.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Just her. Always her.</p><p class=\"action\">They sit in silence for a moment, the weight of the</p><p class=\"action\">observation hanging heavy in the air. The soft weeping nearby</p><p class=\"action\">seems to grow louder.</p><p class=\"action\">They glance across the hall. A patient slams their head</p><p class=\"action\">gently against the table in rhythm with the ticking of a</p><p class=\"action\">broken clock.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We used to hear them walking the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">halls. Buzzers. Carts. That white</p><p class=\"dialogue\">noise. Now it’s just... absence.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Shouldn’t there be nurses?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Schedules? More staff?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I thought that was just maybe</p><p class=\"dialogue\">budget cuts. But this?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">\"Budget cuts.” Yeah. OK.</p><p class=\"action\">Silence.</p><p class=\"action\">In the far corner, a music box begins playing by itself. Its</p><p class=\"action\">warped melody echoes across the tile.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We need a plan.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So we do what? Break in again?</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Confront her? Or we catch her off</p><p class=\"dialogue\">guard. She slips when things go</p><p class=\"dialogue\">off-script.... I'm in.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Yes, confront her. This whole place</p><p class=\"dialogue\">revolves around her. The locked</p><p class=\"dialogue\">door. The symbols. The vanishing</p><p class=\"dialogue\">people. She’s at the center. She’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">not improvising anymore. She’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">reacting. Which means... she’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">afraid.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’ll wait until tonight. When it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">quiet. One of us distracts her. The</p><p class=\"dialogue\">other two gets in. Let’s make her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">afraid again.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Assuming she can be distracted.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She has a weakness. She acts like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">she’s in control, but every time</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something breaks the pattern—she</p><p class=\"dialogue\">stumbles.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So let’s break the pattern.</p><p class=\"action\">They nod. A pact sealed in silence.</p><p class=\"action\">The camera pans wide. The other scattered patients continue</p><p class=\"action\">in their cycles—rocking, crying, whispering. No one</p><p class=\"action\">acknowledges them. The sound of a distant music box plays</p><p class=\"action\">from somewhere unseen.</p><p class=\"action\">CLOSE-UP: a patient in the background begins laughing and crying</p><p class=\"action\">at once, eyes darting back and forth like they’re watching</p><p class=\"action\">something crawl across the ceiling.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. VARIOUS LOCATIONS – LATER THAT NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The hospital begins to falter. Lights flicker wildly. Walls</p><p class=\"action\">pulse like breathing skin.</p><p class=\"action\">The floors groan under invisible pressure. Benjamin, Regan,</p><p class=\"action\">and Otto walk cautiously through the hallway, their eyes</p><p class=\"action\">scanning everything.</p><p class=\"action\">A loud bang echoes from down a corridor.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did you hear that?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Something’s not right. It’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">glitching again. Or unraveling.</p><p class=\"action\">Down the hall, they spot a patient running silently, mouth</p><p class=\"action\">open in a scream—no sound. Hands scrape invisible walls. Then</p><p class=\"action\">the patient freezes, flickers like bad reception, and</p><p class=\"action\">disappears.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The others. They’re not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hallucinating anymore. They’re</p><p class=\"dialogue\">seeing the same layers we are.</p><p class=\"action\">They reach a corridor lined with old hospital beds— stacked,</p><p class=\"action\">rusted, forgotten. One shifts on its own.</p><p class=\"action\">From a room, sobbing erupts, then erupts into manic laughter.</p><p class=\"action\">They pass another room and see someone levitating, limbs bent</p><p class=\"action\">backward, suspended midair. A blink—and it’s empty again.</p><p class=\"character\">CARMILLA (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">(backing in to view,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">shaking)</p><p class=\"action\">Something touched me. But it</p><p class=\"action\">wasn’t... here.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Are we next?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s like... Something’s testing</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the boundaries.</p><p class=\"action\">The hallway pulses again, almost rhythmically. Lights turn</p><p class=\"action\">red, then blue, then return to their usual cold white.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Whatever’s here is losing control.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Or maybe it’s gaining it.</p><p class=\"action\">Down the hall, another patient runs past them, face pale and</p><p class=\"action\">twisted in terror, chased by shadows clinging to the walls.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Agreed. We find Anna. We break out.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And if she’s not who we think?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then we stop pretending any of this</p><p class=\"dialogue\">is what it seems.</p><p class=\"action\">As they walk forward, the hallway behind them slowly darkens—</p><p class=\"action\">like a void swallowing the past.</p><p class=\"action\">They don’t look back.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 27</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON AREA – NEXT MORNING</p><p class=\"action\">The three sit in quiet tension. Outside the windows, the gray</p><p class=\"action\">light flickers unnaturally, stuttering like a dying bulb.</p><p class=\"action\">The air feels heavier than usual. Something unsaid hangs between</p><p class=\"action\">them.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly—</p><p class=\"character\">INTERCOM (DISTORTED)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin Price, report to Dr. Anna’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">office immediately.</p><p class=\"action\">The voice is garbled, deep and echoing. A sharp hiss follows</p><p class=\"action\">before it cuts out.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That didn’t even sound like her.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She never uses the intercom. Ever.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe she's scared. Or maybe she's</p><p class=\"dialogue\">fucking with us.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Either way... this is it.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We’ll be right outside the door. If</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you feel anything’s wrong, knock</p><p class=\"dialogue\">twice. We’ll force our way in.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No matter what she says... don’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">leave.</p><p class=\"action\">They exchange solemn nods. Benjamin rises and walks away without</p><p class=\"action\">looking back.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DR. ANNA’S OFFICE – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin enters. The door shuts on its own behind him. He doesn't</p><p class=\"action\">notice.</p><p class=\"action\">The room is dim, steeped in incense and silence. Candles flicker</p><p class=\"action\">on high shelves, casting fractured light across framed diplomas</p><p class=\"action\">and crystals.</p><p class=\"action\">Anna sits behind her desk, poised as always—yet something is</p><p class=\"action\">different. Her smile is too wide. Her stillness, too perfect.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello, Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How are we feeling today?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Same as yesterday.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And how was your evening? Did you</p><p class=\"dialogue\">rest?</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin starts to answer but trails off—he’s noticed something.</p><p class=\"action\">In the corner of the room sits a young woman. She looks about 17</p><p class=\"action\">or 18, dressed in slightly out-of-place clothing—modern, like she</p><p class=\"action\">walked out of a suburban bedroom rather than a hospital.</p><p class=\"action\">Her fingers move slowly across the floor, tracing invisible</p><p class=\"action\">shapes.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin, do you like puzzles?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Excuse me?</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Puzzles. Little pieces coming</p><p class=\"dialogue\">together. Making something bigger.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Making sense.</p><p class=\"action\">The girl lets out a soft giggle. Benjamin turns toward her, but—</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (SHARPLY) (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t. Don’t pay her any attention.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s not supposed to talk.</p><p class=\"action\">The girl looks up, directly at Benjamin, but her eyes seem to</p><p class=\"action\">shimmer—like light flickering on water.</p><p class=\"character\">GIRL</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He’s going to say it. Just watch.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He’ll answer this time.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (FURIOUS)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Stop it. He’ll answer when he’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">ready!</p><p class=\"action\">Anna’s voice breaks—not like a doctor losing patience, but like a</p><p class=\"action\">teenager snapping at a sibling.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin flinches. Anna quickly recomposes, regaining her tone.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA (GENTLY NOW) (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Tell me about the colors in your</p><p class=\"dialogue\">dreams. Are they vivid?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (AGITATED)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What is this? An intern?</p><p class=\"character\">GIRL (SMILING)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Ask him about the birds.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Enough! You’re ruining it! This isn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a game!</p><p class=\"action\">The room darkens slightly, and the candles flare, casting long,</p><p class=\"action\">warped shadows behind Anna.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin grips the armrest tightly. A high-pitched sound creeps</p><p class=\"action\">into the room— barely perceptible, like a television left on in</p><p class=\"action\">another room.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (QUIETLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think... I think I’d like to end</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the session early today.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Of course. I'm sorry for the</p><p class=\"dialogue\">distraction.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin rises.</p><p class=\"action\">He glances back toward the girl—</p><p class=\"action\">She’s gone.</p><p class=\"action\">Only the empty chair remains, gently rocking.</p><p class=\"action\">He looks back at Anna, whose face remains still, expression</p><p class=\"action\">unchanged.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What are you?</p><p class=\"action\">Anna smiles faintly. A candle near her blinks out.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY OUTSIDE – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Regan and Otto wait in silence.</p><p class=\"action\">From inside the office:</p><p class=\"action\">A faint girl’s laughter.</p><p class=\"action\">A loud knock.</p><p class=\"action\">Then nothing.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The room is dim, lit only by a flickering wall sconce. Shadows</p><p class=\"action\">bend unnaturally along the walls. Benjamin enters slowly, the door</p><p class=\"action\">creaking shut behind him. Regan and Otto rise from their chairs,</p><p class=\"action\">tense.</p><p class=\"action\">He doesn’t speak right away—just sinks into the chair like the air</p><p class=\"action\">has been sucked from his lungs.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What happened in there?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She wasn’t alone. There was a girl—</p><p class=\"dialogue\">just sitting there, like she belonged.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She kept... smiling. Giggling. Like</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the whole thing was funny.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What do you mean “funny”?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t know. But she kept saying I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">was going to “answer.” Like I was</p><p class=\"dialogue\">supposed to... play along.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Anna always knows too much. But</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that... that’s different.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She snapped. Not at me—at the girl.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Lost her composure completely. It was</p><p class=\"dialogue\">like a mask slipped off and something</p><p class=\"dialogue\">else was underneath.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And you just walked out?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t think I was supposed to.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think something broke in there.</p><p class=\"action\">The overhead light flickers, buzzing sharply—then bursts,</p><p class=\"action\">showering sparks. The room dims further.</p><p class=\"action\">A deep pulse vibrates through the floor—faint but undeniable. Dust</p><p class=\"action\">falls from the ceiling. Regan grabs the edge of the table.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s not even pretending anymore.</p><p class=\"action\">A hairline crack splits across the far wall, crawling like a vein.</p><p class=\"action\">The light from the hallway turns blood-red for a moment—then</p><p class=\"action\">fades.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m done waiting around for answers</p><p class=\"dialogue\">that never come.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">We expose her. Trap her. Trick her.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Burn it down if we have to.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No more sessions. No more polite</p><p class=\"dialogue\">questions. Anna’s the one who needs to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">start answering.</p><p class=\"action\">They all fall silent. The air thickens, tinged with the scent of</p><p class=\"action\">smoke, earth, and rot.</p><p class=\"action\">Far in the distance: a scream, sharp and childlike. Malachai.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—total silence. They don’t move. The room pulses once, slow</p><p class=\"action\">and heavy, like a final heartbeat.</p><p class=\"action\">Malachai runs into the room and approaches Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You made trouble! YOU HAD NO RIGHT!</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Come on you little freak.</p><p class=\"action\">Jace grabs Malachai and carries him off.</p><p class=\"character\">MALACHAI</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(screaming, thrashing)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Put me down, you bastard! You don’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">touch me! You don’t get to touch</p><p class=\"dialogue\">me! I’ll kill you, I swear—</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(voice cracks)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ll tear your eyes out! I’ll—</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(breath hitching)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ll... I want my mom.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(sobbing)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I want my mom. Please. I just want</p><p class=\"dialogue\">her. I didn’t mean to stay. I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">didn’t mean it.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quiet, broken)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She said she’d come back. Can I go</p><p class=\"dialogue\">back to her now? Please?! I'll be</p><p class=\"dialogue\">better this time. I promise. I want</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to try again! Why didn't Dad lock</p><p class=\"dialogue\">up the gun?? How was I supposed to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">know??</p><p class=\"character\">FADE TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 28</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DR. ANNA’S OFFICE – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">Otto sits stiffly in the chair across from Dr. Anna. The</p><p class=\"action\">candlelight flickers more violently than usual. The crystals</p><p class=\"action\">on the shelf vibrate ever so slightly. The room seems smaller</p><p class=\"action\">than usual, tighter, warped at the edges.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello, Otto. How are we feeling</p><p class=\"dialogue\">today?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Spare me the routine.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(pause)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Very well. What would you like to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">discuss?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">My assignment. My punishment.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Because that’s what this is, isn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it?</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto, you’re here for your safety.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">For your peace.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">LIES.</p><p class=\"action\">He shoots up from the chair. The candles gutter. The shadows</p><p class=\"action\">in the room twist unnaturally—as if recoiling.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I remember the trenches. The blood.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The sound of artillery—Kaiser be</p><p class=\"dialogue\">damned, I survived worse than this.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And now I’m trapped in your haunted</p><p class=\"dialogue\">dollhouse of lies!</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please calm down.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You speak in riddles. Burn your</p><p class=\"dialogue\">little herbs. You have no idea what</p><p class=\"dialogue\">we’ve seen—what we’ve felt. I was a</p><p class=\"dialogue\">human being once! Now, what am I? A</p><p class=\"dialogue\">pawn? A toy?? What the fuck is</p><p class=\"dialogue\">this??</p><p class=\"action\">He grabs a candle and hurls it against the wall. It hits hard</p><p class=\"action\">—but instead of shattering, the flame simply snuffs out, and</p><p class=\"action\">the room tilts slightly, as if gravity hesitated.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto. That’s enough.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You think I don’t know what’s going</p><p class=\"dialogue\">on? That I’m just some shell-</p><p class=\"dialogue\">shocked relic? I see the cracks!</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The walls breathe. The air hums.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not in charge here.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(standing abruptly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This session is over.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Convenient.</p><p class=\"action\">He glares at her, his chest rising and falling sharply. The</p><p class=\"action\">lights flicker as he clenches his fists. Anna reaches for a</p><p class=\"action\">small bronze bell, old and strange, etched with unfamiliar</p><p class=\"action\">symbols.</p><p class=\"action\">She rings it once.</p><p class=\"action\">The sound is not pleasant—it’s thin, metallic, and somehow</p><p class=\"action\">wet. Like bone dragged across tile.</p><p class=\"action\">A moment passes.</p><p class=\"action\">The door behind Otto creaks open on its own, slow and</p><p class=\"action\">deliberate. Cold air spills in.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please leave, Otto. Goodbye.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You first.</p><p class=\"action\">They lock eyes. Otto’s stare is molten, unwavering.</p><p class=\"action\">Then, slowly, he turns and exits—his gaze never breaking</p><p class=\"action\">until the very last second.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Regan sit at a table, heads close in quiet</p><p class=\"action\">debate. Otto storms in, jaw clenched, eyes wild.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What happened? Are you okay?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She tried to shut me down. But I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">saw it. I felt it.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What do you mean?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">She’s not in charge anymore—if she</p><p class=\"dialogue\">ever was. There’s something else</p><p class=\"dialogue\">behind all this.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I said things she didn’t want to</p><p class=\"dialogue\">hear. Asked questions she couldn’t</p><p class=\"dialogue\">answer.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Did she react?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Like I hit a nerve. She rang some</p><p class=\"dialogue\">kind of bell—sounded like bones</p><p class=\"dialogue\">grinding together. Then the door</p><p class=\"dialogue\">opened on its own.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">So, she is hiding something.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">More than that. She’s afraid.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Good. Let her be. Now it’s her turn</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to feel powerless.</p><p class=\"action\">They exchange a grim look.</p><p class=\"action\">Something in the walls cracks quietly, like a seam splitting.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">At the very least, I rattled her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">cage.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Regan nod in agreement. The shadows behind them</p><p class=\"action\">seem to lean forward, listening.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 29</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – LATER THAT NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">The lighting is dimmer than usual. The corners of the room seem to</p><p class=\"action\">breathe, expanding and contracting almost imperceptibly. The walls</p><p class=\"action\">hum, like a tuning fork struck in some distant part of the</p><p class=\"action\">building.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan and Benjamin sit across from Otto, who is visibly</p><p class=\"action\">unraveling. His leg bounces, his hands tremble, his eyes dart as</p><p class=\"action\">if trying to remember where he is.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto, what is it? You’re scaring me.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t think I’m supposed to be here</p><p class=\"dialogue\">anymore.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What are you talking about?</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Something happened when I yelled at</p><p class=\"dialogue\">her. Something... cracked. I felt it</p><p class=\"dialogue\">inside me, like the floor gave out.</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(beat)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And now I feel like I have to leave.</p><p class=\"action\">He clutches his chest—not in pain, but like he’s holding himself</p><p class=\"action\">together.</p><p class=\"action\">The room hums louder, as though reacting to his words.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">And go where? How??</p><p class=\"action\">Before he can answer, the overhead light sputters, dims to a dull</p><p class=\"action\">orange, then steadies. The air grows heavy—like thick velvet</p><p class=\"action\">pressing down on them.</p><p class=\"action\">A low tone begins. Deep. Resonant. Inhuman.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—</p><p class=\"action\">From the far doorway, two tall, shadowed figures appear.</p><p class=\"action\">Dressed in antiquated white coats, their features are indistinct,</p><p class=\"action\">blurred at the edges like bad reception. Their shoes make no sound</p><p class=\"action\">as they move forward.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto...</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. No, not yet—</p><p class=\"dialogue\">(then suddenly a flicker</p><p class=\"dialogue\">of clarity)</p><p class=\"action\">Wait—</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(realization dawning)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I need to tell you—</p><p class=\"action\">The figures reach him, flanking him without urgency. Each</p><p class=\"action\">takes an arm, and Otto immediately fights, jerking away.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Listen to me! This place— It’s not—</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(he chokes)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh God, how did we not see it?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto!</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m not ready! Please! I’m not—</p><p class=\"action\">The figures begin to drag him.</p><p class=\"action\">His feet scrape across the floor. His voice rises in desperation,</p><p class=\"action\">but there’s a stillness in the room that swallows sound.</p><p class=\"character\">OTTO (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t trust her! Don’t — she's just</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a....</p><p class=\"character\">SLAM.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The door shuts behind him, unnaturally loud. Final.</p><p class=\"action\">A faint echo of Otto’s scream lingers for just a breath... then is</p><p class=\"action\">gone.</p><p class=\"action\">Silence.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Regan don’t move. They stare at the door, eyes</p><p class=\"action\">glassy, bodies tense. The light above them buzzes softly, then</p><p class=\"action\">goes out, leaving only the flicker of red from the hallway.</p><p class=\"action\">The room pulses once, like a final exhale.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN (QUIETLY)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">He was right.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(Through tears)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Oh god....</p><p class=\"action\">They sit in the dark.</p><p class=\"action\">No one breathes.</p><p class=\"action\">The camera holds too long.</p><p class=\"action\">Then—</p><p class=\"action\">In the corner, something moves, but when they turn—there’s nothing</p><p class=\"action\">there.</p><p class=\"action\">The door slams shut behind them.</p><p class=\"action\">Silence.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Regan stare at the door, unmoving, stunned. The</p><p class=\"action\">room pulses once like a dying breath.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 30</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. STAIRWELL LANDING – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">A low whine hums through the air. Red emergency lights flash</p><p class=\"action\">dimly, distorting shadows along the cracked walls. Dust hangs like</p><p class=\"action\">smoke.</p><p class=\"action\">Regan and Benjamin sit huddled on the landing between floors.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin clutches a broken clipboard, Regan trembles—but holds it</p><p class=\"action\">in.</p><p class=\"action\">They’ve been running. Or hiding. Or both.</p><p class=\"action\">Footsteps echo from above.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(sharp whisper)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Someone’s coming.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Stay behind me.</p><p class=\"action\">They tense—until a familiar figure descends the stairs, limping</p><p class=\"action\">slightly.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">REGAN</p><p class=\"action\">Jace!</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Found you.</p><p class=\"action\">He doesn’t smile. His face is streaked with dirt and sweat, and</p><p class=\"action\">his knuckles are scraped.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where have you been?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Watching.</p><p class=\"action\">He sits across from them, leaning against the wall like he’s been</p><p class=\"action\">carrying bricks on his back. He stares at the space between them—</p><p class=\"action\">unblinking.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’re all gone.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Who's gone?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">All of them. Carmilla. Lucy. That</p><p class=\"dialogue\">quiet girl with the drawings. They’re</p><p class=\"dialogue\">not here anymore.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">ALL of them?? Do you know where</p><p class=\"dialogue\">they've gone???</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I saw the orderlies. They came, one by</p><p class=\"dialogue\">one. They don’t all scream like Otto.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Some just... give up.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">How did they take Lucy? She never made</p><p class=\"dialogue\">a sound.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Didn’t have to. She knew. She walked</p><p class=\"dialogue\">with them.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Jesus...</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I thought if I stayed in the vents, or</p><p class=\"dialogue\">in that hallway that loops, they</p><p class=\"dialogue\">wouldn’t see me. But I saw them. I saw</p><p class=\"dialogue\">all of them.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Why are you still here?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t know. Maybe I’m not interesting</p><p class=\"dialogue\">enough. Maybe I’m not healed yet.</p><p class=\"action\">He runs his hand across the concrete floor, smearing old ash into</p><p class=\"action\">the lines between the tiles.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">This place— It doesn’t want to be</p><p class=\"dialogue\">fixed. You have to adapt to it, learn</p><p class=\"dialogue\">it. That’s the game.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">That’s what the girl said... back in</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Anna’s office. Like we were pieces of</p><p class=\"dialogue\">something.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Pieces that get rearranged. Until they</p><p class=\"dialogue\">fit. Or snap.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(low)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I think I’m going to be next.</p><p class=\"action\">They both look at her. Benjamin tenses, but says nothing.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I feel it in my stomach. Like it’s</p><p class=\"dialogue\">already pulling on me. And I’m not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">scared of dying. I’m scared of not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">existing.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’ll still be something. Just not...</p><p class=\"dialogue\">here.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. We’re not losing anyone else.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You don’t get to decide that,</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Then what the hell can I decide?</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s not about deciding. It’s about</p><p class=\"dialogue\">resisting. Stay uncomfortable. Stay</p><p class=\"dialogue\">angry. That’s the only thing they</p><p class=\"dialogue\">can’t control.</p><p class=\"action\">He looks at the flickering stairwell light above. It’s turning in</p><p class=\"action\">slow circles now, like a halo twisted sideways.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You can feel it too, right?</p><p class=\"action\">They all go still. In the distance, a loud CRACK splits the</p><p class=\"action\">silence.</p><p class=\"action\">A scream? Or metal? It’s impossible to tell anymore.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">If they take me... I don’t want to go</p><p class=\"dialogue\">the way Otto did.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You won’t.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I mean it. If you see me walking away</p><p class=\"dialogue\">with them—stop me.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I will.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’ll hurt them if I have to.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They’re not afraid of pain.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe they’ll be afraid of us.</p><p class=\"action\">They fall silent again. The light bulb finally bursts, showering</p><p class=\"action\">glass down the stairwell like quiet rain.</p><p class=\"action\">The three sit in the darkness, back to back, as the sound of</p><p class=\"action\">distant whispers begins to fill the space below them.</p><p class=\"transition\">FADE OUT.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 31</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – EARLY MORNING</p><p class=\"action\">The air is thick. Heavy. Like it’s resisting being breathed.</p><p class=\"action\">Every corner of the room seems darker than it should be.</p><p class=\"action\">The lights buzz, pulsing like a weak heartbeat. Shadows</p><p class=\"action\">stretch unnaturally across the cracked linoleum.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and Regan sit on the floor near the wall, knees</p><p class=\"action\">drawn up, backs barely touching. The silence between them is</p><p class=\"action\">loaded, brimming with things unsaid.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(low)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">My head... It’s like pressure.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Building. Like it’s going to split</p><p class=\"dialogue\">open. You think it’s what Otto</p><p class=\"dialogue\">felt?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No. Don't say that.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe it is the same. Maybe worse.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Maybe I'm dying.</p><p class=\"action\">She grips the sides of her head and shakes slightly, like her</p><p class=\"action\">mind is vibrating apart. Her voice falters, too exhausted to</p><p class=\"action\">cry.</p><p class=\"action\">Suddenly—a low hum fills the room.</p><p class=\"action\">Familiar. Dreadful.</p><p class=\"action\">The kind of sound you feel before you hear.</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stiffens. Regan’s breath catches in her throat.</p><p class=\"action\">From the doorway, two tall, shadowed figures appear. The</p><p class=\"action\">Orderlies.</p><p class=\"action\">Their forms are flickering, as if poorly rendered. Their</p><p class=\"action\">features remain faceless, stretched thin like wax too close</p><p class=\"action\">to heat.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">No.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Please. Help me.</p><p class=\"action\">He grabs her hand. She grips it with desperate force, her</p><p class=\"action\">fingers cold.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t want to go. Not like this.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I don’t even know where I’m going.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Where do they take you?</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You’re not. I won’t let them take</p><p class=\"dialogue\">you.</p><p class=\"action\">The first figure steps forward, gliding rather than walking.</p><p class=\"action\">It reaches out, placing a hand on Regan’s shoulder.</p><p class=\"action\">She gasps sharply, a scream stuck in her throat.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(shaky)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I can’t breathe. Oh God—Benjamin—</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin and orderly fight. He loses after being grabbed and</p><p class=\"action\">thrown down hard. He crawls over to Regan, she sits on the</p><p class=\"action\">floor crying.</p><p class=\"action\">He leans forward quickly and grabs her hands in his, kissing</p><p class=\"action\">her fingers.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m so sorry. For everything. I am</p><p class=\"dialogue\">so sorry I can't stop this.</p><p class=\"action\">Her lip trembles. She’s shaking hard now.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I’m scared.</p><p class=\"action\">The second figure moves in. Places a hand on her arm.</p><p class=\"action\">She begins to thrash, her legs kicking as if caught in</p><p class=\"action\">undertow, nails digging into the floor, scratching gouges</p><p class=\"action\">into the tile.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Stop! She’s not ready!</p><p class=\"action\">He lunges, grabs at the figure’s wrist. It throws him back</p><p class=\"action\">like paper, and he crashes into a chair, ribs smacking hard.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin! Please! Don’t let them—!</p><p class=\"action\">Her scream turns to a sob as she’s lifted from the floor,</p><p class=\"action\">feet dragging, leaving smudged red from her scraped fingers.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">REGAN!</p><p class=\"action\">The lights flicker violently. The walls moan with pressure.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">(realization crosses her</p><p class=\"dialogue\">face, she smile)</p><p class=\"action\">Oh my god..... Benjamin. It's going</p><p class=\"action\">to be OK! Please don’t forget me...</p><p class=\"action\">I will see you soon.</p><p class=\"action\">She reaches back—her fingers so close, but out of reach.</p><p class=\"action\">And then she’s gone.</p><p class=\"action\">The door slams shut behind them with a THUNDEROUS boom.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. COMMON ROOM – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">Benjamin stands still for a full moment.</p><p class=\"action\">He stares at the door.</p><p class=\"action\">And then drops.</p><p class=\"action\">He collapses to his knees, hands hanging limp, shaking.</p><p class=\"action\">Tears begin to fall silently, but his face is blank.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(whispers)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You said you’d stay.</p><p class=\"action\">His breath begins to quicken, turn sharp.</p><p class=\"action\">Then the first sound leaves his throat: a howl.</p><p class=\"action\">A deep, raw, guttural scream that rips up from his chest and</p><p class=\"action\">tears the silence in half.</p><p class=\"action\">He punches the floor once. Twice. A third time.</p><p class=\"action\">Then he just sobs.</p><p class=\"action\">For a long, long time.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. HALLWAY – MOMENTS LATER</p><p class=\"action\">The building rattles, its bones unsettled.</p><p class=\"action\">Smoke creeps from beneath the common room door, rising like</p><p class=\"action\">fog across Benjamin’s shoes as he stumbles down the hall.</p><p class=\"action\">His hands tremble. His eyes are wild. Haunted.</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DR. ANNA’S OFFICE – CONTINUOUS</p><p class=\"action\">The door swings open before he touches it.</p><p class=\"action\">Dr. Anna stands in the center of the room, lit from behind by</p><p class=\"action\">flickering candlelight and rolling smoke.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello, Benjamin. Welcome.</p><p class=\"action\">He steps forward, still trembling, rage boiling over sorrow.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You knew. You KNEW they were going</p><p class=\"dialogue\">to take Regan.</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Regan is gone?? No... I never know.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">But it’s not permanent here. Not</p><p class=\"dialogue\">for anyone. I would help you if I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">could. If I knew how.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Don’t lie to me. You let them take</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Otto. You let them take Regan. You</p><p class=\"dialogue\">sit here on your crystal throne</p><p class=\"dialogue\">like some gatekeeper—</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(shaken)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I never meant for this. My mother</p><p class=\"dialogue\">warned me. She said... She said I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">should never play with things I</p><p class=\"dialogue\">didn’t understand.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Play with what?</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(whispers)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">The board.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">WHAT? We buried that board!</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You weren’t supposed to know. But</p><p class=\"dialogue\">yes. I opened something. I thought</p><p class=\"dialogue\">I could talk to them. Help them.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Help you. But now the door’s too</p><p class=\"dialogue\">wide. Something else came through.</p><p class=\"action\">The smoke thickens. Benjamin stumbles, falls to his knees,</p><p class=\"action\">clutching his head.</p><p class=\"action\">The scent of sage is overwhelming, but rotten underneath.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What’s happening?</p><p class=\"character\">DR. ANNA</p><p class=\"dialogue\">They must be coming. I’m so sorry.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">You were my favorite.</p><p class=\"action\">She backs away, vanishing into the swirling smoke.</p><p class=\"action\">Two hands reach from behind, grab Benjamin by the arms.</p><p class=\"action\">He screams—a cry of raw fear, sorrow, and rage—as he’s</p><p class=\"action\">dragged backward through the fog, through the office, through</p><p class=\"action\">the walls—</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">EXT. LIVING ROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">A teenage girl stands in front of a fireplace.</p><p class=\"action\">The room is quiet, save for the ticking of a clock and the</p><p class=\"action\">flicker of firelight. In her hands: a Ouija board that</p><p class=\"action\">closely resembles colors and patterns of hospital.</p><p class=\"action\">She stares at it, eyes wide. Lips trembling.</p><p class=\"action\">Then, slowly — She throws it into the flames.</p><p class=\"action\">As the flames surround it — The faint sound of Benjamin’s</p><p class=\"action\">scream echoes.</p><p class=\"action\">Then silence.</p><p class=\"character\">FADE TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"shot\">SCENE 32 -EPILOGUE - 3 ENDING OPTIONS</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">EXT. MEADOW – ETERNAL SUNSET</p><p class=\"action\">Soft golden light blankets the field. Wildflowers sway gently. The</p><p class=\"action\">air is warm and calm, filled with birdsong and the hum of distant</p><p class=\"action\">wind chimes.</p><p class=\"action\">BENJAMIN lies in tall grass, eyes blinking open to the sky. His</p><p class=\"action\">brow, once furrowed with fear, is smooth now. He exhales.</p><p class=\"action\">A voice calls from nearby.</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN (O.S.)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Benjamin.</p><p class=\"action\">He sits up.</p><p class=\"action\">She’s standing a few feet away in the field, barefoot in the</p><p class=\"action\">flowers, hair lit like a halo in the sunset. She smiles — real and</p><p class=\"action\">full.</p><p class=\"action\">His eyes fill with tears.</p><p class=\"action\">He walks to her. She meets him halfway, and they embrace like they</p><p class=\"action\">never thought they’d see each other again.</p><p class=\"action\">In the distance, Otto laughs, sitting with Amber and Carmilla</p><p class=\"action\">beneath a tree, playing cards on a picnic blanket.</p><p class=\"action\">No one speaks of pain. Or loss. Or the hospital.</p><p class=\"action\">Only peace.</p><p class=\"character\">BENJAMIN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Is this... real?</p><p class=\"character\">REGAN</p><p class=\"dialogue\">It’s real enough.</p><p class=\"action\">She takes his hand.</p><p class=\"action\">They turn toward the others. Together.</p><p class=\"transition\">MATCH CUT TO:</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. DARK ROOM – UNKNOWN TIME</p><p class=\"action\">A soft scratching echoes in the darkness.</p><p class=\"action\">A dim light reveals JACE, crouched near a crumbling wall, dragging</p><p class=\"action\">a jagged object across the surface.</p><p class=\"action\">Dozens of tally marks scar the space around him.</p><p class=\"action\">One more.</p><p class=\"action\">He leans back. Eyes hollow.</p><p class=\"action\">A sound behind him.</p><p class=\"action\">A door creaks open.</p><p class=\"action\">He doesn’t turn.</p><p class=\"character\">JACE</p><p class=\"parenthetical\">(quietly)</p><p class=\"dialogue\">Hello?</p><p class=\"transition\">MATCH CUT TO:</p><p class=\"action\">​</p><p class=\"scene-heading\">INT. BEDROOM – NIGHT</p><p class=\"action\">A flickering candle casts shadows across a teenage girl’s face as</p><p class=\"action\">she kneels on the floor of her suburban bedroom.</p><p class=\"action\">She pulls a half-burned Ouija board from a thrift shop bag.</p><p class=\"action\">Curious, she places it gently on the carpet.</p><p class=\"action\">She hesitates, then touches a crystal glass lying where a</p><p class=\"action\">planchette should be, but is missing.</p><p class=\"character\">TEEN GIRL</p><p class=\"dialogue\">What’s your name?</p><p class=\"action\">The marker begins to move.</p><p class=\"character\">J... A... C... E.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">TEEN GIRL (CONT'D)</p><p class=\"action\">Hi, Jace.</p><p class=\"action\">The candle flickers violently.</p><p class=\"action\">Somewhere behind her, a shadow stirs.</p><p class=\"action\">She doesn’t notice.</p><p class=\"character\">CUT TO BLACK.</p><p class=\"dialogue\">THE END</p>","Private Pad":"","Title Page":""}